cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဟန်မင်းထွေး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On September 13, the armed wing of the junta raided Kan Oo Village, Yesagyo Township, Magway Region and stationed there for the night. Junta forces then arrested and tortured a local Han Min Htway. On September 14, he was found by the villagers, even though they transported him to Myay Daw Tike Area Hospital, he died in the hospital.

On September 18, at around 9 pm, Lal Madee, an ethnic-Lisu from Ward 2, Arlan Village in Myitkyina Township, Kachin State was killed.  Lal Madee was going to check on his bamboo raft at a pier when he ran into the junta forces. Junta troops tried to stop him, but when he fled in fear, they shot him. During the shooting, family members were warned not to leave their house and their phones were taken away. His body was then set on fire near a river bank.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ခန့်သူရိန်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On the afternoon of September 17, Khant Thurain, age 17, died after suffering from drug-resistant Tuberculosis. He had been sentenced to one year's imprisonment at Insein Prison. Three days before his death, Khant Thurain was sent to the Tuberculosis ward of the prison hospital. On the morning of September 17, he had difficulty breathing and collapsed. His family had to sign a form to retrieve and cremate his body. The form stated that the family must not take photos of his dead body or post about Khant Thurain's death on social media, as not to cause a "riot." The form also stated that if a riot occurs, Khant Thurain's father will be arrested.

On September 17, Light Infantry Battalion 351 station in Natthankwin Bridge indiscriminately shot heavy weaponry into Taung Su Village, Kyaukkyi Township, Bago Region. A local woman named Naw Thoo Lei Phaw was hit and killed by heavy weaponry shrapnel. Locals in Taung Su Village fled outside the village when military troops forcibly located them. After Naw Thoo Lay Phaw returned to the village to retrieve rice, she was struck by the heavy weapon when she was trying to leave the village.

On September 18, Soe Linn Paing and Phoe Sal who were farming near Wat Khot Village, Gway Kone Village Tract, Yesagyo Township, Magway Region. The farmers were killed by junta forces who arrived in the afternoon.

On September 18, Soe Linn Paing and Phoe Sal who were farming near Wat Khot Village, Gway Kone Village Tract, Yesagyo Township, Magway Region. The farmers were killed by junta forces who arrived in the afternoon.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဇော်လပြည့်(ခ) ဇွန်လပြည့်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On September 18, at around 11:20 am, Zaw La Pyae (aka Zune La Pyae), who was sentenced to 7 years in Meiktila Prison under the charges of Counter-Terrorism Law Section-52(A), died because he was not given medical treatment in time. From September 15, Zaw La Pyae (aka Zune La Pyae) began hyperventilating and was short of breath. On September 17, the clinic administered a shot but he got more tired and he was not even able to eat. On September 18, at around 7 am, he was sent to the clinic again where they gave him another shot. But it did not get better so they went there again at around 8 am. However, the 3 prisoners-on-duty sneered at him. Afterwards, he went to the toilet and collapsed while coming down from the toilet. So they sent him to the clinic again at around 9 am and decided to send him to a hospital outside prison. They arrived at the hospital on 10:45 am, but died on 11:20 am. The cause of death was determined to be blockage in the mitral valve (heart). Zaw La Pyae (aka Zune La Pyae) was a train station staff and he took part in Civil Disobedience Movement (CDM).

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On March 23, Private Win Thura, Maung Tu and Kyaw Zin Latt from Light Infantry Battalion (LID) 368, shot dead a local woman from Tha Pyay Aye Village, Yinmrabin Township, Sagaing Region. They then raped her dead body. While the LID junta troops were running away from their base, they were detained by the local defense forces in Yinmarbin Township. Their war crimes were then discovered in Yinmarbin Township and they confessed.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On July 11, junta forces raided Taung Ywar Thit Village, Pale Township, Sagaing Region. It was reported they raped and killed a 13-year old girl.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On March 28, junta forces stationed in Kyaw Village, Mingin Township, Sagaing Region, raped the women in the village, resulting in the deaths of 3 women. The victims were around 14-years-old, 16-years-old, and 35-years-old.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On March 28, junta forces stationed in Kyaw Village, Mingin Township, Sagaing Region, raped the women in the village, resulting in the deaths of 3 women. The victims were around 14-years-old, 16-years-old, and 35-years-old.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On March 28, junta forces stationed in Kyaw Village, Mingin Township, Sagaing Region, raped the women in the village, resulting in the deaths of 3 women. The victims were around 14-years-old, 16-years-old, and 35-years-old.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 4, junta forces raided Htei Hlaw Village, Gangaw Township, Magway Region, and killed a father. Junta forces then proceeded to rape the 16-year old daughter, then killed her and burned her body.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဇွဲနိုင်ဝင်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On September 22, junta forces stationed in Shwe Paw Kyunn Pagoda in Shwegu Township, Kachin State, fired heavy weaponry indiscriminately at villages on the other side of the river in Shwegu. One of the artillery shells exploded in Moe Sitt Village, killing 12-year old Zwe Naing Win on the spot while another woman lost her leg. Other villagers were also injured, whilst 2 households were burnt down.

On September 19, Phoe Taw and another local from Wat Khot Village in Yesagyo Township, Magway Region, encountered junta forces whilst they were drinking palm juice (alcohol) and were detained. On the morning of September 21, Phoe Taw's body was discovered near Sar Hkar Village in Salingyi Township, Sagaing Region, with gunshot wounds on the body.

On September 21, the armed wing of the junta launched an offense into Khin-U Township, Sagaing Region, entering Thar Ga Ya Village and killing Htay Maung, 70-years-old, who was seeking refuge in monastery. His body was then thrown down a drinking well in the monastery.

On September 21, at 1 pm, an junta artillery division, stationed in Loikaw, Kayah State, fired heavy weaponry indiscriminately. 2 of the artillery shells landed into Saung Kan (Shan) Village in Loikaw Township, killing a local named Jue.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: မောင်မောင် (ခ) ရခိုင်မောင်မောင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On September 20, locals from Ka Lone Htar Village in Yebyu Township, Tanintharyi Region sought refuge in nearby forests, mountains and monasteries, to escape an invading column of junta forces. On September 21, at around 5 pm, Maung Maung (aka Rakhine Maung Maung), who was working as a field guard in the village, was stabbed to the death by the junta troops and his body left behind in a rubber plantation field.

On September 25, at around 11 pm, Operation Control Command No.9, based in Kyauktaw Town, Rakhine State, indiscriminately fired heavy weaponry. One of the artillery shells landed on a house in Nagara Village, Kyauktaw Township, killing 7-year old Ko Naing (aka Maung Gyi).

On the morning of September 24, Thaw Zin Oo, a member of Township News and Information and an NLD Ward and Village executive member from Ahnauk Kan Phyu Village, Seikphyu Township, Magway Region, was arrested, tortured, then killed by junta forces.
Arkar Kyaw Moe was killed in a military junta airstrike in Hpakant Township, Kachin State, on September 26, 2021.

On September 24, at around 2 am, Naing Oo, a ethnic-Mon from Kalawt Village in Ye Township, Mon State, was shot dead while going to a rubber plantation. He was shot at by a hidden junta night watch post along the way.

On September 23, at 7:30 pm, Jee Nan, from Ka War Yan Village in Mogaung Township, Kachin State, was shot dead by junta forces. Jee Nan suffered from a mental disorder. She was shot dead when she went near a Light Infantry Battalion-384 and 385 junta base.

On September 22, at 7 am, Saw Arr Htaw Moo from Kyun Pin Seik Village in Kyaukkyi Township, Bago Region, stepped on a landmine after returning from checking his fish-trap. As soon as the mine exploded, junta LIB-603 arrived. Unable to stop the bleeding, villagers attempted to transport Saw Arr Htaw Moo to Kyaukkyi Town but they were prohibited from doing so. They were only able to transport him to Nat Than Kwin. But before they arrived Saw Arr Htaw Moo died from loss of blood at 11 am near Wae Gyi Village ahead of Nat Than Kwin.

On September 25, a column of around 60 junta troops advanced towards Shwebo Town from Khin-U Town, Sagaing Region, and shot at 2 farmers in the fields on the side of a road near Myay Ni Sho Village. Kyaw San Myint died, while Ohn Shwe  was shot in the thigh and seriously injured.

On September 21, at around 1 am, junta forces went into Yone Pin Village in Khin-U Township, Sagaing Region and detained a local called Nyunt Linn. On September 23, the hands of Nyunt Linn were tied behind his back, and he was shot dead.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဇေယျာလင်း (ခ) အဂ္ဂ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On September 27, Zayar Linn (aka Agga), a member of Monywa Township People's Defence Team (Township PDT), was detained by junta forces in Monywa Township, he was inhumanly murdered hours later.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On September 27, at 3:30 pm, Infantry Battalion-250 and Light Infantry Battalion-422, fired indiscriminate heavy weaponry from Loikaw Township, Kayah State. One of the artillery shells landing in Kone Thar Village, Loikaw Township, killed a 55-year-old woman in her house on the spot, whilst two local villagers were also serious injured.

On September 23, Kyaw Naing Win, a teacher from Wundwin Town, Mandalay Region, was arrested by junta police from Wundwin Myoma Police Station and No.99 Light Infantry Division junta troops, due to a false report from a junta informant. On September 27, Kyaw Naing Win died in Meiktila Interrogation Center. His family was informed about his death on September 28. Kyaw Naing Win took part in CDM but due to pressure from the junta, he had to become non-CDM teacher again.

On September 28, Maung Oo from Hnin Nu Village, Indaw Township, Sagaing Region, was taken as a human shield by the junta forces and was later killed at Nant Thae Village. In addition, the junta forces also killed Thein Tan, from Man Hton Taung Gyi Village, Indaw Township, who was beaten and killed in Aung Kone Village. Thein Tan was arrested in Aung Kone Village while going to Indaw Town.

On September 28, Maung Oo from Hnin Nu Village, Indaw Township, Sagaing Region, was taken as a human shield by the junta forces and was later killed at Nant Thae Village. In addition, the junta forces also killed Thein Tan, from Man Hton Taung Gyi Village, Indaw Township, who was beaten and killed in Aung Kone Village. Thein Tan was arrested in Aung Kone Village while going to Indaw Town.

On September 29, at around 4 PM, Win Khaing, who was driving a motorbike with a side-carriage on Thanbyuzayat-Ye Road, Ye Township, Mon State, was shot dead by junta troops in a hidden watch post in the area. Win Khaing was from Mawt Kanin Village and was killed on the spot after getting shot through the head. His body was recovered by community rescue service members and was sent to Lamaing Hospital.

On September 29, at around 5:55 PM, the junta forces from Baw Ka Htar Base, Kyaukkyi Township, Bago Region, fired heavy weaponry into Baw Ka Htar Village. As a result, locals Pauk Sa and Nyar Ma Aye were killed, while a further 5 people were injured.

On September 29, at around 5:55 PM, the junta forces from Baw Ka Htar Base, Kyaukkyi Township, Bago Region, fired heavy weaponry into Baw Ka Htar Village. As a result, locals Pauk Sa and Nyar Ma Aye were killed, while a further 5 people were injured.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: မရန်ဆိုင်းဂူ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 2, at 10:30 PM, Marang Sai Gu, who was riding a motorbike, was shot dead by the junta forces and police near Sone Si Yar Grocery Store in Klub Kone Ward, Hpakant Township, Kachin State. His body was taken away from the hospital that same night. He was shot and killed because he didn't stop, while the junta forces were pulling over vehicles on the road for inspection.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On September 29, at around 8 AM, a mentally-unwell man was shot dead by the junta forces on the ascent of Ayetharyar-Taunggyi Road, in Shan State. He regularly hitchhiked for a ride and on the day he got killed, he was going to work in Taunggyi Town. He got killed because he happened to hitch a ride while a VIP vehicle column of the junta forces was coming. His body was  taken away by the junta forces.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: Due to the junta forces firing heavy weaponry during the 2-day fighting that took place in Tigyaing Township, Sagaing Region, a woman and a novice monk died. On September 29, at around 6 AM, a fight broke out between junta forces and People's Defense Forces near the entrance of Pauk Kone Village. The junta forces fired heavy weaponry at Pauk Kone Village and Ywar Thit Kone Village. As a result, a woman seeking refuge at Pauk Kone Village Monastery was killed by an artillery shell. Furthermore, on September 30 at around 6 AM, another fight broke out near Ti Taw Village, and the junta forces assisted with heavy weaponry from Tigyaing Town. Some of the artillery shells landed in Nawarat Ward and as a result, a novice monk from Wai Pote La Monastery collecting food got his head blown off and died. In addition, a husband and wife were injured.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အောင်ကိုဝင်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: In the afternoon of October 3rd, a car with Area Police Station Commander Police Lieutenant Zaw Win and Air Defense Force Major Zaw Zaw Naing in it, was attacked by the Revolutionary Guerrilla Group coalition in Paleik Town, Sintgaing Township, Mandalay Region, resulting in the death of the 2 men. Subsequently, the junta forces blocked off and searched the area around Paw Taw Mu Temple area where the attack took place, and proceeded to arrest passersby and locals. Additionally, in the evening of October 4, Aung Ko Win, a CDM staff from Paleik Electricity Department, along with a local were killed by junta forces.

On October 3, at 12 AM, Thein Htay from Tada-U Village, Kyaukse Township, Mandalay Region, was arrested in her house by junta forces arriving in 3 military vehicles. She was tortured by the junta. Then on October 4, her family was informed to come and take his dead body covered with injuries consistent with torture.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 6, at around 6 PM, a junta convoy was attacked by a landmine between Nant Oun Village and Twan Mone Village in Nant Salap Village Tract, Hseni Township, Shan State. Following this, junta forces in the convoy indiscriminately opened fired with various weaponry. A local from Nant Oun Village was killed, whilst 2 others from Twan Mone Village and a local from Pan Thee Village were wounded.

On September 29, Pyu Saw Htee militiamen opened fire upon the house of San Myint and Thi Thi Soe in Dagon Myothit (South) Township, killing them on the spot. They were the parents of 17-year old San Min Paing, who had run away from Thanlyin Youth Training School, Yangon Region. Pyu Saw Htee members raided the house and opened fire. San Min Paing was an urban guerrilla youth and was arrested in August 2021. On September 23, 2022, 14 youths, including San Min Paing, escaped from the Youth Training School.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဦးလာဒိန်းလျဲန်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 10 at 11 AM, Lal Ding Lian, who lived in East Kho Bway Ward in Matupi Township, Chin State, died as he stepped on mine while he was cleaning up a farm located near the Lal Myo Chaung Bridge.
He was arrested under Section 505 A of the Penal Code on April 11, 2021, and died on October 9, 2021.
He died at the police station in Ma Mauk village.
Killed in 2022

On 4 May at around 8:00 pm, the armed wing of the junta beat and arrest Aung Mying Hlaing (aka) Ko Kyay, a resident of Pyay Township in Bago region. The next day, Pyay No. 1 police station informed his family that they can see his dead body in the Shwedaung military hospital. The military refused to release his body, so the family cannot hold a funeral for him. The family got to see his body in a coffin with only the head visible, with bruises on his face, throat, and cheeks. The junta arrested Aung Myint Hlaing for questioning related to a bomb blast in front of a branch of the military-owned Innwa Bank, in Shwedaung on April 24. About an hour after Aung Myint Hlaing’s arrest, the troops came back to the same ward and apprehended three more people from the area. Neighbors later told the family that they saw Aung Myint Hlaing after the troops returned, saying he looked like he had been badly beaten and appeared to be unconscious as they dragged him through the street.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ညန်လျန်ဝုန်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On 11 October, at around 9:00 pm, two offices in Myoma ward, Tedim Township in Chin state, were burned in a fire. Infantry Battalion 269 based in Tedim, used unprovoked artillery shelling in the area, killing Ninng Lian Vun from Lai Lui village with an artillery shell while she was sleeping. In addition, a man was hit and injured.

On 8 October, the armed wing of the junta arrested, tortured, and killed two scouting members, Ye Hnin Wai and Hlaing Zaw Oo, of the village Defence Group of Gar Ga Law village, Kanbalu township in Sagaing Region. They were arrested while they were scouting Light Infantry Battalion 367 of around 70 soldiers leaving from Zinn village next to Mandalay-Myitkyina road. On the same day, their dead bodies were found, with many injuries, on the road between Zinn village and Baw village.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 11, the armed wing of the junta and pro-junta militia was on a military offensive operation into Anout Bat Village, Tilin Township, Magway Region, where they killed four innocent civilians. After they left the village on October 13, the four dead bodies were found burnt, tied with ropes at their backs, left in a house that had been burned down.

On October 12, three local villagers who were herding cows in a farm near Hgnet Pyaw Taw Village, Kyunhla Township, Sagaing Region, were accused of being People Defence Force (PDF) and arrested by the armed wing of the junta and pro-junta militia. A 14-year-old child was released, but the two others were tied up with ropes at their backs and were shot dead in Kyauk-I Village. One of the two youths who was killed was Kyaw Htet, from Hgnet Pyaw Taw Village.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ကျင်ဗျက်ဆန်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On September 9, Cin Biak Sang, from Doe Wine Chaung Village, Kale Township, Sagaing Region, was arrested while being checked by junta forces inspecting Bogyoke Road, Tar Han Ward, Kale Town. His family members have not been able to contact him since he was arrested. On October 14, junta forces informed the family to come collect his body. His family said there were a lot of injuries on his back. However, the junta told the family on phone that Cin Biak Sang died from injuries sustained after getting drunk and losing control and warned the family not to tell the media this.

Maung Ngal, who was sentenced to 5 years in prison under Counter-Terrorism Law Section Section 52, died in Loikaw Prison on October 13, after being denied adequate medical care. In 2021, he was arrested at a checkpoint in Loikaw and charged with Counter-Terrorism Law Section 52, after being accused of connection to the PDF. His family is still unable to recover his body.

On the morning of October 12, junta forces raided Ka Toe Village in Budalin Township, Sagaing Region, and detained youths at a house of wedding ceremony. Allegedly because they were PDF. Junta troops then proceeded to torture them. On October 13, the junta column left the village and took with them 5 youths as hostage. They let 3 of the youths go, but Kyaw Myint Oo and Zaw Min Khaing, who were a part of village security, were tortured and killed.

On October 15, at around 10 AM, junta forces raided Nga Lone Tin Village in Chaung-U Township, Sagaing Region, after firing various weaponry. Almost 300 households were burned down and 3 locals died named Yan Aung, Min Thant and Kyaw Gyi. Junta forces thereafter continued destroying Ma Hti Thar Village and killed a local villager, Sein Win.

On the morning of October 16, a junta convoy entered Thit Nyi Naung Village in Pauk Township, Magway Region and arrested the head of Pyin Nyar Moe boarding school, Saw Tun Moe. Junta troops tied his hands on his back and abducted him. On October 17, Saw Tun Moe was beheaded and his legs and hands were cut off. The beheaded head was hanged on the gate of Taung Myint Village Middle School. Saw Tun Moe is involved in CDM, and teaching at the school opened by the National Unity Government.

On October 17, at around 12 PM, junta forces, stationed in Pyayar Ma Mountain in Minbya Township, Rakhine State, fired heavy weaponry into Palong Byint Village. In consequence, two sisters; 23-year-old Hla San Yin and 10-year-old San Nwel Soe, and Oo Mya Sein were seriously injured. Although Hla San Yin, one of the two sisters, was transported to Pauktaw Hospital, she died at around 3 PM. San Nwel Soe died at around 4 PM while seeking treatment in Thit Pote Taung Clinic.

On October 17 at around 7:30 pm, Yar Mi Nar, living in Upper Pike Thae Kan Pike Village in Kyauktaw Township, Rakhine State, was struck by a heavy weapon on her thigh while at home. The shell was fired in the house by the armed wing of the junta stationed in Kyauktaw Mountain. Yar Mi Nar was severely injured and died while being transported to Ah Pauk Wa Station Hospital.

On October 17 at around 3 pm, a primary school teacher named Ma Mya Saw, who was teaching at Daunk Chaung Gyi Village School, was killed on the spot by an artillery shell. Battalion #541 located in Minbya Township, Rakhine State, fired the shell which landed near the entrance of the school. Ma Mya Saw was hit as she left the school having dropped off the children.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: မာမတ်အီနုရ်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 18 at around 11 am, Mamad Einu, living in Dine Nat Pyin Village in Sein Hnyin Pyar Village Tract, Buthidaung Township, Rakhine State, was injuried on his stomach, right arm and thigh by an artillery shell fired by battalion #551. Mamad Einu was at his betel nut farm when he was hit, and died after being transported to Buthidaung Hospital.

cellValuesByColumnId.fld7KLBHB6DdATjnu: U Aung Kyaw Min + Daw Thein Nu
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 19, at past 11 am, the armed wing of the Junta stationed at Ye Soe Chaung Base in Rathedaung Township, Rakhine State fired three artillery shells indiscriminately into Pyeinn Taw Village. One shell landing in the village killed 14-year-old Nyein Nyein San on the spot.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ညွန့်ညွန့်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 19 at around 10 am, Nyunt Nyunt and a six-month pregnant woman named Soe Soe, were killed by a junta airstrike near Pyar O Tan Village. The pair were living in Nown Tan Village in Yinmarbin Township, Sagaing Region. They were running away from the junta when the junta launched an airstrike near Yin Paung Taing Village.

On October 19 at around 10 am, Nyunt Nyunt and a six-month pregnant woman named Soe Soe, were killed by a junta airstrike near Pyar O Tan Village. The pair were living in Nown Tan Village in Yinmarbin Township, Sagaing Region. They were running away from the junta when the junta launched an airstrike near Yin Paung Taing Village.

On October 19 at around 5 am, Myint Oo was shot dead at the fence entrance of his house while retrieving his ill father as locals ran away from a junta raid on the village. Myint Oo had a hearing disability and was living in Shwe Bon Thar Village in Myaung Township, Sagaing Region.

On October 19 at around 3 pm, kindergartens 6-year-old Henry Bawi Za Lian and 7-year-old James Siang Za Uk, were killed by a junta artillery shell and another child was injured. The children where hit whilst returning home from school at Buanlung Khua Village in Hakha Township, Chin State.

In the evening of October 17, San Aye, a political prisoner detained in Pathein Prison, Ayeyarwady Region, died from lack of oxygen. San Aye was from No.5 Ward in Pathein Township and was arrested for anti-junta protests. He was charged under Counter-Terrorism Law Section-52 (a) and his family was not allowed to cremate his dead body.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: နှင်းအိလွင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: In the morning of October 23, a 12-year-old called Hnin Ei Lwin from Sin Gone Taing Village was killed by artillery. Indiscriminate heavy weaponry was shot by a junta convoy carrying rations from Katha Township in Sagaing Region to Bhamo Township along the Ayeyarwady River.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 20, at around 11 PM, troops from 104th junta IB #104 troops and Pyu Saw Htee militiamen detained and killed four locals from Launglon Township, Tanintharyi Region. Their names were Maung Soe Tin, his wife Khin Nwet, adopted son Thet Oo, along with Zayar Tun (aka Ko Zay). All were killed in the house of Maung Soe Tin and had their heads shot up, faces swollen with bruises from beatings, with Khin Nwet had her throat slit.

On October 20, due to a landmine attack by a local PDF on a junta column leaving Yin Paung Taing Village in Yinmabin Township, Sagaing Region, gunshots were exchanged and Daung Min PDF leader Sakka and a fellow comrade were injured and detained. They were severely tortured, killed, and heads and body parts cut off, by the junta troops.

On October 23, at around 8:30 PM, junta forces bombed a music ceremony in Hpakant Township, Kachin State with 3 fighter jets. The strike killed artists, civilians, members of the Kachin Independence Army (KIA) and members of other organizations. According to recent reports from a local rescue team member, deaths exceeded over a hundred. However, in-charge of information at the KIO announced it is inconvenient to reveal the victims of A Nang Pa bombing due to junta investigations on surviving family members. Therefore, it is difficult to collect and document precise numbers and identities of the fallen.

On October 20, at around 4 PM, the junta forces fighter planes bombed an area while there was an opening ceremony taking place at a hospital in Man Yue Gyi Village, Banmauk Township, Sagaing Region. Local Khin Mar Cho died on the spot, while 6 children were seriously injured. The hospital was destroyed and 5 households burned down.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 23, at 9 PM, IB-422 (Infantry Battalion) of the junta forces, situated in Mongpai, fired heavy weaponry near Kone Thar Village, Loikaw Township, Kayah State. One of the artillery shells exploded near a farm hut where a family was seeking refuge. A man was killed on the spot, while his wife was seriously injured in the head and their 8-year-old son was also injured in the thigh. Although the injured woman was transported to Loikaw Hospital, she passed away due to her injuries on October 24, at around 5 PM.
On October 22, at 6 AM, while the junta forces were raiding the base of the group Fight For People in Monywa District, Sagaing Region, Wai Yan, a member of said group was captured and shot dead.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 21, at around 1 PM, junta forces bombed a hospital, staff housing, and a hall in Kyaung Lal Village, Banmauk Township in Sagaing Region, with 2 fighter planes. As a result, a local man was killed instantly, and a woman was injured.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ

On October 25, at around 5 AM, a junta force column opened fire at Magyi Oak Village, Budalin Township, Sagaing Region, with various weaponry, and raided the village. During the process, Nyo Lone, a local, was shot dead while trying to run away, while 3 other locals were injured.

On October 22, at 8 PM, junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee members shot at Maung Soe, a local of Myeik, unprovoked while he was driving a dump truck in Pyigyimandaing Town, Bokpyin Township, Tanintharyi Region, killing him on the spot.
On October 22, junta LIB 599 shot dead Naw Day Nyar from Ta Khawt Pwar Village, Kyaukkyi Township, Bago Region, in an unprovoked shooting.

On October 22, at around 10 PM, the junta forces followed and opened fire on a car near the traffic light on 35th Street and 73th Street, Mandalay Town. As a result a Mandalay local, jade merchant Sein Win, who was in the car, was killed and the jade in his car went missing. The junta forces also confiscated his car. The authorities allowed his family to come and see his body, but did not return the body. Instead, the junta forces had cremated Sein Win's body on their own accord.

On October 26, at 4 AM, an artillery shell fired by the junta forces exploded near a house in Warikawku Village, Loikaw Township, Kayah State. Due to the shelling, 3 family members inside the house were injured. One of them, Kamiyo Puha, was fatally injured in the left arm, ankle and in the head, later succumbing to his wounds.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 26, at 12:30 PM, an artillery shell fired by the junta forces exploded in Pi King Kawku Village, Loikaw Township in Kayah State. A 5-year-old child riding a bicycle was killed, while a further 3 locals were injured in the attack.

Accused of having connections with People's Defence Force, George Maung Ngal was arrested at a Loikaw checkpoint in Kayah State on April 30, 2021. He was then sentenced to serve 5 years in prison on charges of Counter-Terrorism Law Section 52. Denied of proper healthcare inside Loikaw Prison, he died on October 13. His body was not returned to his family.
On October 24, at around 3 PM, junta LID 33 situated in Sagaing, fired heavy weaponry at Paukkah Village in Sagaing Township, Sagaing Region, killing Thein Oo and wounding a further 7 people.

On October 26, the armed wing of the junta situated in Bhamo Township, Kachin State, fired heavy weaponry indiscriminately. One of the artillery shells exploded in a farm in Man Khun Village, killing Thein Htay, who was cutting weeds in the farm.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 27, at around 12 PM, an artillery shell fired by OCC-12 (Operations Control Command) of the junta, landed and exploded on a house in Ward 7, Kawkareik Township, Kayin State, killing a woman, while her husband and her child were seriously injured. A further 15 civilians around the area were additionally injured.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 28, at around 5 AM, the junta forces raided P-ramma Village, Myaung Township, Sagaing Region, after having fired heavy weaponry. They then shot dead a disabled person left behind in the village, who had been unable to run.

On October 28, at 9:20 PM, junta LIB-351 and IB-60 opened fire with heavy weaponry. Some of the artillery shells landed and exploded in a pasture of Thit Cha Seik Village in Kyaukkyi Township, Bago Region. As a result, local villager Ye Min, who was working in the farm, died on the spot while his younger brother was injured.

On October 31, at around 11 PM, Operations Control Command-9 (OCC-9) situated in Kyauktaw Township, Rakhine State, opened fire with heavy weaponry indiscriminately. One of the artillery shells landed and exploded near a household in Pi Si Village, Kyauktaw Township, resulting in the deaths of 3 sleeping family members in the household. They were Soe Win, Than Than Wai (aka) Pu Kay and their 14-year-old daughter Phyo Phyo Wai who was a Grade 6 student. Four of their cattle also died along with them.

On October 30, a junta column of around 100 troops, launched an offensive into Ywar Thar Ywar Village, Indaw Township, Sagaing Region. They then beat and killed 17-year-old Aung Myo Min, accusing him of being a graduate trainee of the People's Defense Force. The forces had left his body on the side of a road. He was arrested because he ran into the junta column in the village, after which they discovered pictures of him graduating from the PDF training on his phone.

On October 29, eleven rows of refugee tents, housing around 300 refugees from Lae Pin Village, Paungde Township, Bago Region, were set on fire by junta forces. The forces also killed and ate a cow owned by the refugees. Then, they took away a refugee, Phoe Wa (aka) Thein Zaw. On November 1, the junta forces rested for a night on Kyoe Pin Mountain, and then tortured and killed him. They also set fire to 5 houses around the place they killed him.

On October 31, at around 7:40 PM, LIB-590 of the junta forces fired 3 artillery shells at Htee To Lo Village, Kyaukkyi Township, Bago Region. One of the shells landed near the house in the village of 78-year-old Chat Thay, resulting in her dying on the spot from shrapnel injuries in her head and stomach.

On November 1, at around 9 PM, junta forces, situated in Ywa Ma Village, Kawlin Township, Sagaing Region, fired heavy weaponry indiscriminately. One of the artillery shells landed on a household in San Tao Ya Kone Village; killing husband and wife Soe Myint and Pu.

On November 1, at around 9 PM, junta forces, situated in Ywa Ma Village, Kawlin Township, Sagaing Region, fired heavy weaponry indiscriminately. One of the artillery shells landed on a household in San Tao Ya Kone Village; killing husband and wife Soe Myint and Pu.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ပိုင်ဆက်မှူး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On November 3, at around 2 PM, a column of junta forces situated in Koe Taung Bolt Village, Kanbalu Township, Sagaing Region, opened indiscriminate fire at nearby villages with heavy weaponry. One of the artillery shells landed on a household in Zee Ka Nar Village, killing 13-year-old Paing Satt Hmue on the spot. His grandmother, who suffered serious injuries in her stomach, died from her wounds in the morning of November 4.

On November 4th, in the morning, the armed wing of the junta shelled villages with artillery in Kyauktaw Township in Rakhine State. A 26 civilians were injured, and three people died. The fatal victims are Maung Tu (80 Years), Aung Min Naing (8 Years) from Shwe Pyi Thit village, and Aye Than Nu (41 Years) from Wat Mhine village.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အောင်မင်းနိုင်

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: နေလင်းစိုး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On 1 November at 5 in the evening, Nay Linn Soe, a resident from Dala Township, Yangon region, returned home from work. When he was at the checkpoint in Sarparchaung Kyaung Su ward, on Dala-Twantay main road, soldiers from the checkpoint arrested him because he couldn’t show his ID. They tied up his legs with a rope, his mouth was closed and he was beaten to death. After that, the forces dragged him out and gave him to the family members. While Nay Linn Soe was being beaten, his mother, and ward elders, begged them not to kill him, but a soldier pushed her away. Nay Linn Soe lived near the checkpoint.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အနိုင်ယွန်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: In the afternoon of November 4, Infantry Battalion 247 junta convoys came down from Namhkan Township to Mong Wee Village, in Shan State. After land mines were detonated, hitting the Battalion, the junta troops opened fire on people harvesting rice in the field nearby, killing two locals: Ah Naing Yun and Ah Yeh Yeh from Mansat Village. Ah Naing Yun was shot dead in the face. Ah Yeh Yeh who was also shot, had his neck and ears cut off, and he was stabbed in the stomach and the back.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အဘူနော်ဆဲရ်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On 5 November at around 11 am, artillery shelling from No. 15 operational command headquarter, in Buthidaung Township, Rakhine State, exploded in Tha Yet Kin Ma Nu Village. Abu Naw Sal died, and a 5-year-old child and 32-year-old woman were injured in Buthidaung township.

On October 23, a junta force column retreating to IB-50 in Kan Village, Gangaw Township, Magway Region, killed mahut* Myat Linn Oo, from Po Oo Village, and Htay Win, from Kun Zae Village, at Hkwa Stream southeast of Myin Zar Village. *A mahut is an elephant rider, trainer or keeper.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: မြတ်လင်းဦး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 23, a junta force column retreating to IB-50 in Kan Village, Gangaw Township, Magway Region, killed mahut* Myat Linn Oo, from Po Oo Village, and Htay Win, from Kun Zae Village, at Hkwa Stream southeast of Myin Zar Village. *A mahut is an elephant rider, trainer or keeper.

On November 2, a junta force column of around 150 troops, from Northwestern Command Headquarters situated in Monywa Town, Sagaing Region, raided villages south of Budalin Township. On the day of the raid, they captured scouting local PDF leader Wai Phyo Aung in Kan Swal Village area. When the junta column left Kan Swal Village, the body of Wai Phyo Aung was discovered at a white hemp plantation near the village. His chest had gunshot wound.

On November 3, at around 2 PM, a column of junta forces situated in Koe Taung Bolt Village, Kanbalu Township, Sagaing Region, opened indiscriminate fire at nearby villages with heavy weaponry. One of the artillery shells landed on a household in Zee Ka Nar Village, killing 13-year-old Paing Satt Hmue on the spot. His grandmother, who suffered serious injuries in her stomach, died from her wounds in the morning of November 4.

On November 8th, the armed wing of the junta and police entered into Kyat Sar Pyin Village, Dawei Township, Tanintharyi Region, at night. They arrested Kyi Lwin, father of Aung Khaing who is a member of Dawei People’s Defence Force, and an unknown male. On November 9th, in the morning, the dead body of Kyi Lwin was found with his hands tied behind his back and blindfolded on New Road in Dawei Township.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On November 7th, at 8 p.m., the armed wing of the junta fired heavy weaponry into Shein Ma Kar Village, Wetlet Township, Sagaing Region. As one piece of weaponry hit and exploded on a house in the village, a woman died and her three family members were injured.

On November 6th, at 9 p.m., the armed wing of the junta and pro-junta militia stationed in Wat Poke Village, Myaing Township, Magway Region, and fired heavy weaponries. As that weaponry hit a house in Chaung Oo To Village, leading to an explosion, 60-year-old Kyee Sein was killed on the spot and his wife, Sein Sint, lost her leg.

On October 23, at around 8:30 PM, junta forces bombed a music ceremony in Hpakant Township, Kachin State with 3 fighter jets. The strike killed artists, civilians, members of the Kachin Independence Army (KIA) and members of other organizations. According to recent reports from a local rescue team member, deaths exceeded over a hundred. However, in-charge of information at the KIO announced it is inconvenient to reveal the victims of A Nang Pa bombing due to junta investigations on surviving family members. Therefore, it is difficult to collect and document precise numbers and identities of the fallen.

On November 8th, at 4 p.m., locals had to flee as a battle broke out between the armed wing of the junta and a local defence force, near Pyar Village, Myingyan Township, Mandalay Region. On November 9th, at 6 a.m., the armed wing of the junta killed a local villager, Zaw Myo Naing, when he entered the village bringing back a bullock cart.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: မောင်မောင်သိန်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: During the evening of November 10th, junta forces entered Sin Inn Gyi Village, Ponnagyun Township, Rakhine State, where they shot 9 locals to death. In the morning of the 10th, junta forces had fired heavy weaponry and an air strike in the area. This attack happened after a junta supply truck was hit by a mine from the Arakan Army (AA), between Paday Thar Bin Village and Sin Inn Gyi Village. Sin Inn Gyi Villagers sought refuge in a monastery whilst some people remained in the village to watch over their houses, of whom 9 were killed that evening.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 25th a people's administration office in Falan Pin Village, Pale Township, Sagaing Region, was attacked by the junta's air force. Next, a special commando force raided the village. During the raid, a Grade-8 student returning from school, a local from Flan Pin Village, and a member of the local defence force, all ran into the commando column by whom they were captured and killed.

On 11 November at around 9:00 am, Aye Soe Thein and Kyar Chay, from Di Par Yone village, Ponnagyun Township in Rakine State, returned from releasing cows outside the village. During their return, an artillery shell exploded close to them, fired by Ponnagyun base Battalion 550. Aye Soe Thien died as a result of the explosion, having been fatally injured in the head. Kyar Chay was seriously injured, having broken his collar bone and dislocated his right thigh, and died on the way to the hospital.

On November 5, at around 5 in the evening, Hein Min Kyaw was arrested by the armed wing of the junta while he was using a phone at the entrance of his village. Hein Min Kyaw was a worker from Yuzana palm oil factory in Bodar village, Bokpyin township in Tanintharyi Region. On November 9, Hein Min Kyaw's body was found shot in the head near Bodar village. Two phones, a gold ring, and some money were on his person when he has arrested, and the soldiers had taken all of these.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On November 7, the armed wing of the junta took two villagers, Phoe La Pyae and Sein Thant, hostage during a military offensive operation approaching Wet Pyit village, Ayadaw township, Sagaing region. Their hands were tied, and they were shot dead in their heads at close range, near Kywe Chan village on Ayadaw-War Taw Ma road.

On 10 November, the armed wing of the junta entered Ywar Shay village in Budalin township, in Sagaing region. They killed an NLD party campaigner Shan and Maung Aung Myo Thant, a 14-year-old. On 11 November, locals found their bodies near the village, in a pigeon pea field.

On November 13th, a military junta column of 60 troops launched an offensive into Htan Gyi Village, Wetlet Township, Sagaing Region. The junta troops killed five locals, burned their bodies and burned down local houses. Four of the locals were members of the People’s Defence Force (PDF) from Pauk Kan Village. Ah Ngal Kaung, Nga Zane, Lu Lay and Zaw Thin, the PDF members, were arrested and killed when they went near Htan Gyi Station, thinking that the troops had left the village. Their bodies were found in a house near Htan Gyi Station on Mandalay-Myitkyina Railway Road. Thin Ko, another local, had been left behind due to poor health and was unable to escape the troops. His body was found in a burnt house in the village.

On November 9th, two members of the People's Defence Force, Mee Tauk and Myo Thu Win, evacuated trapped locals from their village due to shelling. While they were moving through Thet Shay Kan Village, Budalin Township, Sagaing Region, they encountered an armed column of the junta, who shot and arrested them. Subsequently, the junta forces tortured and shot them to death. Mee Tauk’s hands had been broken, his back and abdomen had been stabbed with a knife and his intestines were protruding from his stomach.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On November 11th, the armed wing of the junta fired on Si Thar Myay Village, Ye-U Township, Sagaing Region with four attack helicopters for about twenty minutes. Following the attack, two transport helicopters dropped off troops who then raided the village. The junta forces arrested and tortured three members of the People's Defence Force who were trapped in the village, shot them in their heads and killed them. Those three PDF members were two 20-year-old men, and a 40-year-old teacher who had joined the Civil Disobedience Movement.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အိမ့်သူထက်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On November 7th at 8:30 p.m., Eaint Thu Htet, who was detained by the junta in Obo Prison, Mandalay Region, died of a cardiac arrest. He had been prosecuted under Section 505 B of the Penal Code. In the evening of September 17th, he needed an emergency medical treatment, but was not allowed to receive medical care.

The armed wing of the junta and pro-junta militia Pyu Saw Htee, stationed in Kyaw Village, Taung Twin Chaung Area, Mingin Township, Sagaing Region, raided Kone Maw Village. Kone Maw Village is located over a mile away from Kyaw Village, and was raided on November 8th. That day, the troops burnt houses in the village, and also killed Htay Linn, a local with poor mental health.

On October 29th Thant Zin Oo, who lives in Twantay Township, Yangon Region, was arrested by the armed of the junta for allegedly being associated with People’s Defence Force. His wife, Aye Thandar, their two daughters, aged 13 and one, and four men visiting Thant Zin Oo’s family house to celebrate Kahtein trees, were also arrested. Thant Zin Oo was tortured and interrogated at 70 Infantry Battalion, about a mile south of Twantay Township. Thant Zin Oo’s wife and two children were released after two days of detention. Thant Zin Oo was severely tortured by the armed wing of the junta and members of pro-junta militia Pyu Saw Htee, leading to his death a week after being arrested. Although the junta informed his family about his death, his body was taken to the Mingaladon Military Hospital without it being returned to his family.

On October 23, at around 8:30 PM, junta forces bombed a music ceremony in Hpakant Township, Kachin State with 3 fighter jets. The strike killed artists, civilians, members of the Kachin Independence Army (KIA) and members of other organizations. According to recent reports from a local rescue team member, deaths exceeded over a hundred. However, in-charge of information at the KIO announced it is inconvenient to reveal the victims of A Nang Pa bombing due to junta investigations on surviving family members. Therefore, it is difficult to collect and document precise numbers and identities of the fallen.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On November 16th, three locals died on the spot, and another four were injured, as a shell of heavy weaponry exploded into Chaung Tu Village. The shell had been fired from 539 Battalion based in Kan Sout Village, Kyauktaw Township, Rakhine State. The three locals killed are Khin Maung, Aung Kyi Maung and Phyu Thar Tun. The shell had exploded as they were sitting in a house in the centre of the village.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On November 16th, three locals died on the spot, and another four were injured, as a shell of heavy weaponry exploded into Chaung Tu Village. The shell had been fired from 539 Battalion based in Kan Sout Village, Kyauktaw Township, Rakhine State. The three locals killed are Khin Maung, Aung Kyi Maung and Phyu Thar Tun. The shell had exploded as they were sitting in a house in the centre of the village.

On November 16th, 11 locals died and at least 24 were injured, as shells fired from No.24 Kyein Chaung Inspection Gate and No.7 Border Guard Police Division in Maungdaw Township, Rakhine State, exploded onto Gyake Chaung Village, Maungdaw Township. The shells hit three houses, as local villagers had run into their homes and gathered, after hearing the sound of small weaponry.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ရှာလုမ်ဗန်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On November 15, at 10:30 PM, an artillery shell fired by IB-266 of the junta forces landed and exploded in front of Moe Hein Drinking Water Business building, in Kyaw Bote Ward, Hakha Town, Chin State. As a result, 14-year-old Shalom Van died instantly, while two men were injured seriously.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On November 16, a junta vehicle was hit by a mine, after leaving Muse (105) Miles, Shan State. As a result, the junta forces indiscriminately fired heavy weaponry around the area. The indiscriminate firing killed a person, who was fixing a car on the road nearby.

On November 15, at 5:30 PM, an artillery shell fired by junta forces landed and exploded on a nursery school in Demoso Township, Kayah State. This resulted in 5-year-old Ma Tee being injured in his thigh. She did not receive treatment in time and died as a result of bleeding from the wound. Her 8 family members were also injured due to the shelling. The family had come from Kone Thar Village to seek refuge.

On November 20, at around 2:30 PM, a patrolling junta vehicle going from Thabya Village, Launglon Township, Tanintharyi Region, to Launglon, came across two young men on 2 motorbikes driving towards them. The junta patrol tried to halt the motorbikes, but the young men attempted to flee so the patrol shot at them, killing one of the two. The remaining biker's whereabouts are unknown. In addition, 16-year old Thabya Villager Aung Wai Yan was shot during the patrol's attack, while he was riding a motorbike on the street nearby. He died due to blood loss en route to the hospital.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On November 20, at around 2:30 PM, a patrolling junta vehicle going from Thabya Village, Launglon Township, Tanintharyi Region, to Launglon, came across two young men on 2 motorbikes driving towards them. In addition, 16-year old Thabya Villager Aung Wai Yan was shot during the patrol's attack, while he was riding a motorbike on the street nearby. He died due to blood loss en route to the hospital.

On November 20, at around 7 AM, junta soldiers shot Kywae Chan Villager Myint Soe near the Win Ka Phaw Village bridge, Thayetchaung Township, Tanintharyi Region. Myint Soe lost consciousness, having been shot in his shoulder and leg, after which the junta carried him to Thae Chaung Gyi Police Station. He died from his wounds at the police station and his body has not been returned to his family. He encountered the soldiers while going to the bridge by motorbike and was shot at while he tried to turn around and flee out of fear.

On November 16, an artillery shell was fired from No.24 Kyein Chaung Inspection Gate and No.7 Border Guard Police Division in Maungdaw Township, Rakhine State, which exploded in Gyake Chaung Village Maungdaw Township. The shelling caused the death of 11 locals and an additional 24 people were injured. Of the injured, 16-year-old Ngwe Paing ultimately died on November 18, while seeking medical treatment in Sittwe People's Hospital.

On November 17, at 4:30 PM, BGF-1011 Battalion, led by 2nd Company Commander Lieutenant Nyein, fired with various weaponry into Mi Kayin Village. This resulted in the deaths of 2 locals, 7-year-old Naw Khaing Thazin Khin and 27-year-old Saw Aung Myint Tun, who died instantly, and injured two other people.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On November 17, at 4:30 PM, BGF-1011 Battalion, led by 2nd Company Commander Lieutenant Nyein, fired with various weaponry into Mi Kayin Village. On November 19th, Haung Kyone None and Nu Sei had gotten lost while a battle was going on near Bwarl Thae Village.Junta troops beat and killed Haung Kyone None, a disabled person, in Bwarl Thae Village, Falam Township, Chin State. His body was found in the morning of November 22nd. His body showed wounds from being beaten on his back with a stick, and two bullet wounds between his ribs. Nu Sei is a person with poor mental health, who was additionally arrested by the junta troops.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On November 21 morning, three civilians died when the armed wing of the junta fired heavy weaponry on Taung Ka Lay Village during a clash. Junta forces also used aircraft to attack the village, located in Kyaikmaraw Township, Mon State. Among the three civilians who died, was a male traveler, who was hit by heavy weaponry and died as a result. The two other casualties are local residents, a 15-year-old girl and a 40-year-old man with poor mental health, who died due to the airstrike. In sum, ten people were injured,  five of whom were severely injured.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On November 21, at 11:50AM, local villager Pi Run Neih Kim, was killed in an explosion from the junta’s heavy weaponry fired into the yard of her house in Sal Gyi Village. The artillery shot was fired indiscriminately from a junta base in Kale Township, Sagaing Region.

On November 16, an artillery shell was fired from No.24 Kyein Chaung Inspection Gate and No.7 Border Guard Police Division in Maungdaw Township, Rakhine State, which exploded in Gyake Chaung Village Maungdaw Township. The shelling caused the death of 11 locals and an additional 24 people were injured. Of the injured, 16-year-old Ngwe Paing ultimately died on November 18, while seeking medical treatment in Sittwe People's Hospital. In addition, six-month-old Saung Wai died on the night of November 21, while receiving medical treatment in Maungdaw District People's Hospital.

A junta column raided Paung Lel Kone Village, Khin-U Township, Sagaing Region, and set the village on fire, on November 18 and 19. As a result, two locals died. One of them is 85-year-old blind woman Chit Su, who died in the fire. Another casualty is San Win, who was struck by an artillery shell as he was trying to flee from the village, on November 19.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ရဲမင်းနောင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On November 23, a junta column entered Aung Thar Yar Village, Khin-U Township, Sagaing Region, where they killed 14-year-old grade five student Ye Min Naung and Village Defence Force member Tun Tun Win. Ye Min Naung was shot dead in a field about a mile from the village, after he tried to run away as the column entered the village. Tun Tun Win was captured when he tried to scout the column near that same field. His body was found with a gunshot wound in his chest and he had been decapitated.

On November 23, junta forces attacked Mone Hla Village with Mi-35 fighter plane and around 80 junta soldiers who raided the village. Mone Hla Village is situated in Khin-U Township, Sagaing Region. Due to the heavy weaponry that was fired, 50-year-old Mya and a 7-year-old boy were killed.

In the afternoon of November 23, a junta vehicle carrying 8 junta soldiers was hit by a mine. Afterwards, the junta forces opened fire in the surrounding area, resulting in the death of Marip Mung Jat Aung, from Kalat Kone Ward, Hpakant Township, and the injury of another person.

After junta soldiers were struck by a mine near the Aung Moe Intersection, Yesagyo Township, Magway Region, on November 11, the troops arbitrarily arrested 3 civilians. The civilians in question were tortured by the junta soldiers; they were beaten with rifle buttstocks and were killed by being doused in gasoline and set on fire. The victims were Mar Mar Myint from Pay Kone Village, student Tin Moe Swe from Nyaung Pin Su Village, and Win Ko Oo from Baung Bae Tan Village.

On November 26, at 6 AM, junta forces attacked Than Moe Taung Village, Late Tho Area, Thandaunggyi Township, Kayin State, with 2 attack helicopters. May Lay, a civilian, died instantly and some households were destroyed during the attack. May Lay was from Taungoo Township and was visiting Than Moe Taung Village when the attack took place.

On November 26, at 7:30 AM, a junta column of around 80 soldiers set fire to Myit Taw Village and Kan Thit Village, Khin-U Township, Sagaing Region. The junta column additionally shot and killed Hla Win, a local from Myit Taw Village.

On 24 November, at around 5:00 PM, Raju, a young Gorakh man, the owner of a money transfer business in Tamu township in Sagaing Region, was returning home to Myo Ma ward (Nang Phalong market). After he passed Kan Gyi Wa bridge, a Phy Saw Htee group detained him and shot dead in the head, somewhere in the forest behind the monastery. More than 300,000 Indian rupees (nearly 100 Lakhs of Kyats), a motorbike and a phone were taken from him.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On 24 November, at around 7:00 PM,  two young men, both driving a motorbike on No. 3 Highschool road in Katha township, Sagaing region, were chased by an armed wing of the junta police on patrol. The junta police shot and killing a 30-year-old motorbike passenger, a Katha resident, and additionally seriously injured of one of the motorcycle drivers.

On 25 November, around 5:30 PM, the armed wing of the junta military column entered and opened unprovoked fire with 50 troops and 2 vehicles, in Nwarmathin village, Ayadaw township, in Saging Region. They burnt the village and killed Htay, a blind person, who was burnt alive.

On November 26, junta forces raided Myin Daung Village, Khin-U Township, Sagaing Region, and taking 8 locals. Five of the locals were released, the remaining 3 captives were killed by the junta forces. Nay Soe and Tin Win Myint were burned alive, while the third, Zaw, was beaten to death.

Kyaw Khaing Oo, a local from  Thayetpinsu Village, Khin-U Township, Sagaing Region, was killed by junta soldiers and Pyu Saw Htee members from Ywa Thit Kone Village. His body was discovered on November 28.

In the morning of November 25, around 40 junta soldiers entered Nyaung Pyin Village, Launglon Township, Tanintharyi Region, and took Kyaw Soe as well as Lay War Sar, who was mentally ill. They were taken to the cemetery where they were beaten and killed, after they were questioned.

In the morning of November 25, around 40 junta soldiers entered Nyaung Pyin Village, Launglon Township, Tanintharyi Region, and took Kyaw Soe as well as Lay War Sar, who was mentally ill. They were taken to the cemetery where they were beaten and killed, after they were questioned.

On November 28, at around 4 PM, a junta column raided Myaing Lel Village, Maung Htaung Village Tract, Sagaing Township, Sagaing Region. They proceeded to threaten and beat up locals. Another local, 87-year-old Win Sein, witnessed these acts taking place and suffered a cardiac arrest, killing her.

On December 1, two local women were burnt to death and more than 150 houses were destroyed by fire as a column of the armed wing of the junta raided and set fire to Sar Htone Ywar Thit Village, Salingyi Township, Sagaing Region. The two deceased women are 90-year-old blind Than Ngwe and 85-year-old A Mar Gyi who had previously had a stroke.

On December 3, at 1 p.m., the armed wing of the junta - stationed at Indaw Myoma Police Station, Indaw Township, Sagaing Region - fired heavy weaponry. Their heavy fire struck and exploded at the entrance of Nan Ma Hote Gyi Village, Indaw Township. 14-year-old Thein Htike Kyaw, from Nan Kin Village, who was harvesting rice at the village entrance died, and his three family members were injured. Thein Htike Kyaw’s feet were hit, causing him to bleed to death.

On November 30, a column of the armed wing of the junta, consisting of 70 troops, raided and set fire to Maubin Village, Shwebo Township, Sagaing Region. Five locals died during the raid. On December 1, the bodies of these five locals were found. The deceased are Tin Nyo, Kan Nyein, Kyaw Oo, Win and Than Pu. Win, who was hiding in her house, was hit by a bullet and died. Her son, Kyaw Oo, was shot at close range. Tin Nyo and Kan Nyein had mental health issues.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဘုန်းမြတ်ကို
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 1, 17-year-old Bhone Myat Ko, a local of Lewe Township, was arrested by the armed wing of the junta at 6 p.m. He was suspected of a sound bomb explosion that happened in the morning near a traffic police station, near the intersection of Bo Gyoke Bronze Figure, Lewe Township, Nay Pyi Taw. In the morning of December 4, Bhone Myat Ko’s death was reported to his family. He was a student who joined the Civil Disobedience Movement.

During the afternoon of December 4, two civilians, who were driving a motorcycle together in Doe Wine Chaung Village, Kale Township, Sagaing Region, were arrested, tortured and killed by the armed wing of the junta. The two civilians, Khote Pee and Nga Wine, were detained before they were able to reach the 3S Gas Station and the entrance sign of Doe Wine Chaung Village.

During the afternoon of December 4, two civilians, who were driving a motorcycle together in Doe Wine Chaung Village, Kale Township, Sagaing Region, were arrested, tortured and killed by the armed wing of the junta. The two civilians, Khote Pee and Nga Wine, were detained before they were able to reach the 3S Gas Station and the entrance sign of Doe Wine Chaung Village.

While 17 villagers from Tar Taing Village, Khin-U Township, Sagaing Region were fleeing from columns of the armed wing of the junta in Shwebo Township and Tabayin Township on December 3, they were detained by junta troops. One of villagers was shot dead and one was later found alive. The other 15 villagers were forced to follow the armed junta column, and are still missing. The villager who was confirmed to have died is 52-year-old Mann.

On December 9, while around 10 junta soldiers were extorting money from a drug dealer in Kyun Hla Kone Village, Kawlin Township, they inspected 3 youths, whose identities are still unknown, passed in front of the house. After checking their phones, the junta soldiers beat them up and took them to Kyun Hla Police Station. Afterwards, at around 9 PM, when three of them were getting beheaded on War Yone Kone Road, Gat Bo, Lone Kwe and Tut Pi witnessed the event, and they were shot dead in the head. Their bodies were discovered in the morning of December 10 on a street near War Yone Gone Village, Kawlin Township, Sagaing Region.

After checking their phones, the junta soldiers beat them up and took them to Kyun Hla Police Station. Afterwards, at around 9 PM, when three of them were getting beheaded on War Yone Kone Road, Gat Bo, Lone Kwe and Tut Pi witnessed the event, and they were shot dead in the head. Their bodies were discovered in the morning of December 10 on a street near War Yone Gone Village, Kawlin Township, Sagaing Region.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 10 and 11, the armed wing of the junta set fire to and destroyed: Muu Ka Twin Village, Let Yet Kone Village, Nyaung Gyi Kone Village, Mae O Village, Tha Yet Taw Village and Nyaung Hla Village, all located in Tabayin Township, Sagaing Region. As a result, an elderly man from Mae O Village was burned to death.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: သိန်းအောင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: From December 9 to December 12, 224 houses were set on fire and destroyed in Kokko Kone Village, Pay Pin Chaung Village, Nyaung Kone Village, Zee Phyu Kone Village and Shaw Phyu Kone Village, within Kawlin Township, Sagaing Region. The perpetrators include nearly 60 junta troops from 363 Light Infantry Battalion, stationed in Koe Taung Bot, Kanbalu Township, and an additional 70 junta troops from 369 Light Infantry Battalion, stationed in Chat Thin Area. In the evening of December 11, the armed wing of the junta entered and set fire to Pay Pin Chaung Village, where they killed five civilians. The five civilians are Thein Aung, Ae Maung, Naing Win Tun, Kan Min Soe and Myint Soe.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 7, a 21-year-old Than Htike Zaw (aka) Eh Lwan, a member of GZ-21 Loikaw under Karenni Revolutionary Army (KRU), who lost during Kone Thar Battle happened in Demoso Township, Kayah State, was arrested and killed by the armed wing of the junta.

On December 11, 40-year-old and 32-year-old men were arrested by the armed wing of the junta between Kyauk Sa Yit and War Yaung Villages in Ayadaw Township, Sagaing Region. Two men, members of People’s Defence Force, were tortured, shot head by the junta troops and died.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 13, at 9 a.m., the armed wing of the junta from 427 Light Infantry Battalion and Karenni Nationalities Defence Force (KNDFB-09) had a battle in Loikaw Township, Kayah State. A 36-year-old civilian was hit and died from explosion of an artillery shell fired from the junta at 11 a.m on that day.

On December 11 and 12, 122 houses were destroyed and Phoe Kite who has a poor mental health was burned to death as the armed wing of the junta raided and set fire to Mote Si Village, Ye-U Township, Sagaing Region.

On December 8, a 18-year-old Aung Paing Soe, a member of People’s Defence Force was arrested on Monywa-Pathein Road, west of Lin Sar Kyat Village, Salingyi Township, Sagaing Region. On December 9, his dead body was found.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: During the night of December 10, junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee militia entered Phwar Saw Village, Myaung Township, Sagaing Region where they opened fire indiscriminately. The indiscriminate fire resulted in the deaths of three villagers, while another two villagers were injured. The deceased have been identified as Da Tha (aka) Myo Thu, Zin Ko and Myo Swe.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဗျက်ဇလိန်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 12 and 13, junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee militia raided Nan Chaung Village, Kale Township, Sagaing Region, setting fire to the village. This resulted in around 28 households burning down, and the death of 50-year-old elderly Byak Zalain. Byak Zalain was not fully mobile, resulting in him dying in the fire.

In the morning of December 8, 2022, 80-year-old Sein Maung, from Inn Tain Village, encountered a junta column on Zee Thaung Bridge. Sein Maung was on a visit to Zee Thaung Village, Tigyaing Township, Sagaing Region. During the encounter junta soldiers shot him in the head, point blank, killing him.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: သင်္ကြန်မောင်မောင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: Wah Yaung Villagers 19-year-old Thingyan Maung Muang, 30-year-old Moe Aung and 33-year-old Min Min Aung were taken as hostages during a junta offensive into western Ayadaw Township, Sagaing Region, on December 11, 2022. On December 13, their bodies were discovered in the jungle, 6 miles from where they were detained. According to locals, the junta column responsible for the murders was Ayadaw-based No (10) Military Boot Camp and No (5004) Armored Division.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: six local men, Mandalay Region, Myingyan Township, Ywar Thit Village, were captured by the armed wing of the junta and found dead bodies with injuries in nearby villages. Two bodies were found between Gaung Kew Village and Kan Village, north of Myingyan Township, two bodies, another two corpses were found near Thin Pywun Village on the Myingyan - Natogyi Road, and two corpses were found near Thagyi lake west of Ywar Gyi Village.  Those are Min Thu, Kaung Kaung, Aung Than Kyaw, ‌Aung Zayar Phyo, Aung Naing Win and Zaw Naing Win. The bodies of the 6 were discovered on December 14, 2022, 16 days after they were arrested on November 29 by the 88th Division of the Armed Wing of the Jun during a raid on Ywar Thit Village, Myingyan Township.

Junta forces, who were launching an offensive into Tigyaing Township, Sagaing Region, detained Htay Win Hlaing on December 8, 2022. He was detained about 5 miles to the north of Tigyaing Town, at Pauk Kone Village. During their advance towards Pauk Kone Village, Ye Pauk Gyi Village and Myaing Thar Yar Village, the junta took Htay Win Hlaing with them. Although Htay Win Hlaing was healthy at the time of the detainment, he died on December 11, 2022, the day he was let go by the junta forces in Myaing Thar Yar Village. According to a witness who discovered his body, his head, legs, and arms were full of injuries.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 9 and 12, 224 households from Kawlin Township, Sagaing Region were set on fire in Kokko Kone Village, Pay Pin Chaung Village, Nyaung Kone Village, Zee Phyu Kone Village and Shaw Phyu Kone Village. The fires were started by around 60 junta soldiers from LIB-363 stationed at Koe Taung Bot, Kanbalu Township, and around 70 junta soldiers from LIB-369 stationed at Chat Thin Area. Moreover, during the evening of December 11, the junta forces killed Myint Ko, shooting him in the head and the back

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အိုက်အောင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: From December 7 to December 12, the junta launched daily air-strikes in Kone Thar Village, Namhsan Township, in the Ta'ang (Palaung) Self-Administered Zone, Shan State. As a result, one local died while two people were injured and transported to Myothit Taik Area Hospital. One of them, a local named Aike Aung died on December 13.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 14, junta forces set fire to Ywar Mi Tha Village, Kone Thar, Ywar Thit Village and Chan Thar Village in Ye-U Township, Sagaing Region, and fired heavy weaponry into them. This resulted in the deaths of 2 locals from the artillery shelling.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 14, junta forces set fire to Ywar Mi Tha Village, Kone Thar, Ywar Thit Village and Chan Thar Village in Ye-U Township, Sagaing Region, and fired heavy weaponry into them. This resulted in the deaths of 2 locals from the artillery shelling.

On December 15, a clash broke out between KNLA and junta forces near Lane Pin Wae Village in Shwegyin Township, Bago Region. During the clash, 50-year-old Kyaw Oo Soe was killed by an artillery shell.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ထက်ဘုန်းနိုင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: In the morning of December 16, two children were killed by a military junta unexploded ordnance in Yin Paung Taing Village, Yinmarbin Township, Sagaing Region. The armed wing of the junta carried out air-strikes here in August 2022. The two killed children were five-year-old Htet Bhone Naing and seven-month-old Hein Thura Kyaw.

In the morning of December 16, two children were killed by a military junta unexploded ordnance in Yin Paung Taing Village, Yinmarbin Township, Sagaing Region. The armed wing of the junta carried out air-strikes here in August 2022. The two killed children were five-year-old Htet Bhone Naing and seven-month-old Hein Thura Kyaw.

Meiktila-based Division-99, a junta military division, arbitrarily arrested and tortured Kyar Nyunt. The Division did this after a Pyu Saw Htee member was killed in Kyar Nyunt's village, Thae Taw Lay Village, Wundwin Township, Mandalay Region. The military division accused him of having connections with the PDF. On December 10, 2022, he was shot dead in his hut in the field.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ရွှေဘိလျန်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 15, 2022, Shwe Bi Hlyan, from Tain See Village, Matupi Township, Chin State, was going to visit his aunt at Gangaw Town by motorbike. On his way there, he drove past No(1) Checkpoint, at the entrance of Gangaw Town, without stopping, which led to the soldiers shooting at him from the back, killing Shwe Bi Hlyan. He had to be buried in Gangaw Town, because the troops did not let his body to be carried back to his village.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 13, 2022, junta forces launched an offensive into Sanpya 6-mile and Bet Talain Villages in Demoso Township, Kayah State. This led to three clashes between the junta forces and KNDF-B09. During the clashes, the junta forces fired heavy weaponry indiscriminately, with 3 artillery shells landing inside Daw Sae Village in Demoso Township, killing a local.

On December 17, Tin Moe, a owner of Nilar Electrical Appliances Shop in No.3 Ward, Natogyi Town, Mandalay Region, was not found by junta soldiers and Pyu Saw Htee members. They arrested his wife Lei Lei instead, who was five months pregnant. On December 18, Lei Lei's body was found beside a road in Yone Kone Village, 3 miles to the southwest of Natogyi Town. Her body was found with stab wounds in the stomach and chest, and her throat was slit.

On December 6, junta soldiers and Pyu Saw Htee members took six NLD members from their homes in Natogyi Township, Mandalay Region. Afterwards, they killed all six. In the morning of December 7,  their bodies were found on the road connecting Min Village and Natogyi-Myingyan Road. Their hands were tied behind their backs and they were blindfolded, with bullet wounds in their heads. Their names were Kyaw Saung, Khin Maung Sein, Min Zaw, Han Tin, Soe Paing and 17-year-old Aung Ko Min. All were from Min Village, about 5 miles to the west of Natogyi Town.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: သန်းမြင့်ဆွေ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: During the night of November 3, junta soldiers arrested four locals, including some NLD members, from Natogyi Township, Mandalay Region. They were arrested in their homes, under the guise of checking their visitor lists. The next morning, their bodies were discovered with gunshot wounds. The victims were Than Myint Swe from No.8 Ward and Aye Myat Mon (aka) Bae Oh from No.7 Ward, who were NLD members from Natogyi Town. Furthermore, the third victim was NLD supporter Saw Shwe from Hsu Phyu Kan Village. The fourth victim was an unidentified man. Than Myint Swe, Aye Myat Mon (aka) Bae Oh and the unidentified man's bodies were found near Zay Date Village. Saw Shwe's body was found near Let Pan Village. Both villages are in Natogyi Township.

On December 18, locals were harvesting rice paddies in the fields of Hsin Inn Village, about 21 miles west of Shwebo Town, Sagaing Region, when police and Pyu Saw Htee members came and opened fire. This led to the death of local Maung Win from Maubin Village, the 65-year-old owner of the fields, who was killed due to being shot in his back. The Pyu Saw Htee members had come from Ku Doe Seik Village, Nyaung Kaing Village and Myin See Village.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အောင်နိုင်ထွန်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: From December 16 to 18, a battle broke out between the armed wing of the junta and joint forces of the Kachin Independence Army (KIA) and People’s Defence Force (PDF). The battle took place near Pain Inn Village, Gyone Gyone Kya Village and Nyaung Kone Village in Indaw Township, Sagaing Region. While nearby villagers were fleeing the battle, the armed wing of the junta arrested four civilians. They shot and killed all four near the monastery in Pain Inn Village. Their names are Aung Naing Tun from Nant Thae Village, Nay Win from Kwin Chaung Village, Kyaw Lwin from Ma Au Kone Village and an unknown man from Indaw Township. On December 20, buried bodies were found near the monastery.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဝင်းလွင်စိုး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: According to CDF-Zotung's statement on June 21, a junta column launching an offensive into the area where CDF-Zotung was active, arrested 6 locals and killed 2 of them. The offensive began from June 4 and the junta forces used 6 captive locals as human shields. Afterwards, they killed 2 of them; Win Lwin Soe (28-year-old) and Myint Maung (55-year-old), were shot dead on June 11 and June 12 respectively, according to the statement. Both villagers' bodies were discovered on June 18 and 21 and they were given proper funeral, according to the CDF.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 20, 2022, 50 junta troops raided Sel Village, Myaung Township, Sagaing Region, where they arrested and killed Myat Thu Aung. Myat Thu Aung was a member of the local People’s Defence Force, who was on guard for community security when he was taken. After killing him, the troops burnt his body.

On December 18, 2022, two men, Aung Cho Win and Maung Maung, who lived in Htan Pin Kone Village returned to the village after they had taken shelter. They took shelter outside the village in Kyunhla Township, Sagaing Region to avoid conflict and take food and supplies. On their way back, they encountered the armed wing of the junta, by whom they were shot and killed. The two died on the spot.
