On December 19, Pyu Saw Htee members from Htan Kone Village entered Zee Pin Thar Village, Kanbalu Township, Sagaing Region and where they asked villagers to enlist as part of their group. This resulted in an argument with two locals. The Pyu Saw Htee started shooting causing 13-year-old Thu Ta Zaw to run away, during which he was shot. He died before receiving medical treatment. In addition, the Pyu Saw Htee burnt and destroyed two houses in the village.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: In the morning of December 19, the armed wing of the junta stopped and checked an express bus coming from Dawei, at the Palaw Bridge checkpoint on Myeik-Dawei Road, Palaw Township, Tanintharyi Region. A male passenger of the express car, who was identified by the junta troops as suspicious, was severely beaten and interrogated. When the passenger resisted, they shot him with a pistol. After being shot, he was sent to Palaw Hospital, but he died of haemorrhaging upon arrival at the hospital. The armed wing of the junta cremated his body the same day and allowed no one near his burial site.

On December 22, a clash broke out between the junta forces and a coalition of KNLA and PDF at Tadar Kyoe Village, Kawkareik Township, Kayin State. During the clash, an artillery shell fired by the junta landed in Kawt Nwe Village, injuring Phoe Sanay, a former boxer. He died from blood loss that day, due to being struck in the thigh.

On November 28, Infantry Battalion #301 under #88 Division based in Magway Town, Magway Region, entered Nat Ma Hote Gyi Village, Indaw Township, Sagaing Region. The military column detained 8 civilians. Among them, two were tied hands behind their back and beheaded. The other 6 were beaten to death and their heads blown apart. On December 25, those 8 dead bodies were found in the forest near Kan Ni Village, Indaw Township in Sagaing Region. 3 of the dead bodies had been buried in one hole, and other five dead bodies were found in a separate hole. The victims were Kyaw Than, Bo Bo Wai, Min Naing, Kyaw Htay, Kyaw Tun, Tun Naing, Myint Phay, and Thar Pyuu.

They detained Nyi Nyi Aung (16 years) and Win Hlaing (50 Years) as human shields before killing them both. On December 22, their dead bodies were found on the side of the road close to Kyat Tha Yay Chaung Village.

On December 24, at around 11 AM, junta troops fired indiscriminate gunfire from the corner of Bogyote Street and We Zali Hospital Street where they were stationed in Tahan Ward, Kale Town in Sagaing Region. One local was killed and another was injured. The casualties were from Pyin Kone Gyi Village, Kale Township. They were passing by near We Zali Hospital on a motorbike when the soldiers shot at them. Thian Zei Thang's right chest was shot, as he was sitting at the back. He later died from blood loss, while the motorbike driver was shot in the arm.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ပွင့်သူနိုင် (ခ) ဘဲဥ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 23, a Hein Star Express bus travelling on Monywa-Pyinoolwin Road, near a visiting-ward in Nyaung Pin Hla Village in Sagaing Township, Sagaing Region, was indiscriminately shot at by junta division #33 troops in a military vehicle. A female passenger died from a gunshot wound. Her name was Pwint Thu Naing (aka Bae U) from Tone Taung Village, Pyinoolwin Township in Mandalay Region.

In the morning of December 23, 2 Vigo cars carrying junta soldiers were struck by a landmine between Nyin Maw Village and Launglon Town in Tanintharyi Region. Following this, junta soldiers searched the local forests. 17-year-old Phyo Ko from Nyin Maw Village, who was herding cows at the edge of Sii Own Jungle, was shot. Phyo Ko died from blood loss from the gunfire to his buttocks area.

On December 22, around 80 personnel in a junta column fired at Wae Daunk Village, Mawlaik Township, Sagaing Region with various weaponry and raided it. During the process, 9-year-old Khant Phyo Thu was shot dead while he was trying to seek refuge.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 22, at around 9 PM, military junta troops from Kyaukhtu Artillery battalion fired heavy artillery into Kyaukhtu Town in Magway Region. One of the explosions in Gon Bo Ward killed a 6-year-old girl who lived in the ward. She died after being hit by a shell in the head.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဇာနည်နိုင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 21, the armed wing of junta troops based in the east coast of Nyaung Pin Kwin Village in Tanintharyi Township, Tanintharyi Region fired artillery unprovoked. The shelling injured at least 6 civilians in Nyaung Pin Kwin Village and Ban Law Village. A 17-year-old called Zar Ni Naing who was severely injured in the head, died on December 22. She died near Palauk Town, where she was being taken to Yangon Hospital from Myeik.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 17, Light Infantry Battalion 368 and pro-militia Pyu Saw Htee fired artillery on Gargalaw Village in Kanbalu Township, Sagaing Region. The armed group then raided, opened fire, and burned houses, a village clinic and monastery. They also killed 3 men. 2 women who were arrested with the 3 killed men have not yet to be found.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 23, at around 10 AM, junta forces stationed in Kaing Village, Myingyan Township in Mandalay Region, fired heavy weaponry. A 4-year-old child was killed. The artillery shell landed on the house of his grandmother in the village. The grandmother was severely injured, whilst the grandson died during transit to seek medical treatment.

On December 23 , a column of the armed wing of the junta raided and burned down several houses. Ba Latt (85 Years) was burnt alive, in Taung Village, Kyauk Sout Village Tract, Myaing Township in Magway Region.

On December 21, #33 division junta troops and Pyu Saw Htee militiamen from Nyaung Ngote Toe Village raided and set fire to Lin Yin Village, Bauk Thout Village, Lin Yin Ywar Thit Village, Kone Gyi Village and Shan Kone Village. All these villages were in Moe Thout (Bauk Thout) Village Tract in Sagaing Township, Sagaing Region. 700 houses were destroyed and three locals were killed in the rampage. Among the three dead locals, an 80-plus year old called Aye Myaing from Lin Yin Village was burnt to death when she could not escape. Whereas, Phoe Htoo and Min from Moe Thout Village were detained and then killed.

The victims were Sein Maung Myint, Kyaw Tin, Sein Aung, Naing Win Swe, Myo Naing, Swe Linn Aung and Thu Kha from Ye Zin Village. The bodies of Sein Maung Myint, Kyaw Tin, Sein Aung and Swe Linn Aung were discovered in Mi Gyaung Tat Village on December 25, and the bodies of Naing Win Swe, Myo Naing and Thu Kha were discovered to the south of Kalar Village, 7 miles from Ye Zin Village, on December 26.

He was then tied to his motorbike and set on fire alive. A bullet wound was discovered on his charred body.

On December 30, an artillery shell fired by junta forces exploded in San Khar Village, Lone Khin Village Tract, Hpakant Township, Kachin State; injuring six locals. Kun Jar Naw was one of six injured locals and he died on arrival at the hospital.

Military soldiers also detained a local called Nga Hmay for just wearing long pants, then tortured before killing him in a cornfield outside the village.

on January 3, at around 7:30 PM, the junta fired heavy artillery, despite no clash occurring, at Demoso Township in Kayah State. One of the artillery shells exploded on a hut near Daw Tangoo Village, resulting in the death of an internally displaced woman called Soe Myar, who was struck in the thigh.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 22, 2022, seven civilians including six women were arrested by the armed wing of the junta in Matupi Township, Chin State. The junta tortured them in interrogation on a hill of military strategic importance based in Matupi. Among those arrested, De Zin from Van Kaing Village, Matupi Township, was not allowed to meet her family members for more than six months. Therefore, De Zin died from being tortured by the junta soldiers in June, 2022 when her family asked authority. De Zen's death certificate was also issued by the Matupi Township Court.

On January 3, junta troops and Pyu Saw Htee raided Min Village, Natogyi Township, Mandalay Region, detained three villagers named Nyein, Thaung Tan and Zaw Htwe. On the morning of January 4, the dead bodies of Nyein and Thaung Tan were found at the fork of the road to the Gway Pin Yoe Village in Natogyi Township. Zaw Htwe was found with severe injuries in the same place and was receiving medical treatment at the Natogyi Public Hospital.

The junta attacked with three aircrafts, killing Myo Thet Kyaw whose head was blown off, and 30 other people were injured.

On January 7, at around 1 PM, the junta forces fired heavy weaponry after a clash broke out between junta forces and local PDFs near Hsar Dwin Village, Tigyaing Township, Sagaing Region. The artillery shells exploded inside Htan Kone, Kan Pauk and Lay Thar villages, resulting in the death of a woman on the spot, while three people were injured. The deceased was Kyi Pyo from Htan Kone Village.

In the morning of January 6, junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee members raided Tabayin Kwe Village, Sagaing Township, Sagaing Region. They shot and killed Khin Su Mon and Ashin Ganda Tha Ra, who was a temporary resident of Shwegu Monastery and one of the Ten Patrons who graduated from Sitagu Buddha University. Moreover, during the raid, the junta column captured local villager Myo Tun and killed him by hitting him in the head.

A junta column entered Kyar Ta Kan Village, Kyunhla Township, Sagaing Region, and took local villager Nyi Nyi as a hostage. On January 6, the junta column raided Htan Kone Village, also in Kyunhla Township, and set it on fire. When the villagers who fled during the raid returned to Htan Kone after the column left, they found the body of Nyi Nyi with his hands tied behind his back and a bullet wound in his head.

On January 7 at around 7:30 p.m, LIB-207 of junta forces based in Thein Za Yat indiscriminately fired heavy weaponry at Thongwa Village in Kyaikto Township, Mon State. No clash was taking place. An artillery shell exploded to the west of Thongwa Cemetery, killing Zaw Moe Lwin and injuring six of his family members, including seven-year-old Htet Myat La Min.

On the morning of January 9, following a clash between junta forces and regional defence forces in Tigyaing Township, Sagaing Region, an artillery shell fired by the junta exploded on a Htan Kone Village monastery. Seven people were injured and Kyaw Khin, who had been internally displaced, was killed.

On January 8 at around 9 p.m., IB-442 of the junta forces fired heavy weaponry indiscriminately at Mongpai Town, Shan State, without any battle taking place. One of the artillery shells exploded on a house in Pwae Kone (1) Ward, Mongpai Town, killing township resident Lyo Pan who was in the house.

On the morning of January 4, the dead bodies of Nyein and Thaung Tan were found at the fork of the road to the Gway Pin Yoe Village in Natogyi Township. Zaw Htwe was found with severe injuries in the same place but he died on January 5 while he was receiving medical treatment at the Natogyi Public Hospital.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldHfL2UA8oU0Imne: Wai Yan Phyo (aka) Yar Su (aka) Shwe Yoe
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On the evening of January 5, a dispute occurred between prison authorities and political prisoners inside Pathein Prison in Ayeyarwady Region. Prison authorities shot the prisoners with deadly weapons, used a sound bomb against them, tied their hands behind their backs, and severely beat them. Several political prisoners were injured in the dispute. As a result of the prison authorities' actions, political prisoner Wai Yan Phyo (aka) Yar Su (aka) Shwe Yoe died on January 6. The junta did not return Wai Yan Phyo’s body to his family, and at the time of cremation, his family members were only allowed to watch from a distance.

On the morning of January 9, Lal Lian Thawng came to Kale Township, Sagaing Region, from Falam Township, Chin State. At 6 p.m. that day, while he was driving his motorbike across a junta checkpoint near Wal Sali Hospital Fork, Tar Han Ward, Kale Township, he was shot dead by the soldiers on guard. His body was found near the old Letpanchaung Bus Stop on the morning of January 10.
On January 9, junta forces raided Inn Tai Lay Village, Tabayin Township, Sagaing Region, and set it on fire. As a result, 85-year-old local villager Wun Mya died in the fire as he could not run away.

On January 9, junta forces set Set Pyar Kyin Village, Tabayin Township, Sagaing Region, on fire. The forces also shot and killed an 84-year-old Phoe Tar who was sitting on a chair. They disposed of his body by burning it.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 17, 2021, Zaw Naing Oo (aka) Wa Tote (aka) G9, from Hlaingtharya Township, Yangon Region, was arrested by the junta. The junta informed his family that he died from a stomach ulcer at the hospital in Thayet Prison on January 5, 2023.

On January 3, NLD party member Myo Linn from Htain Kan Gyi Village, Myittha Township, Mandalay Region was arrested by the junta. On January 5, his family members were told to come to the hospital because he was sick, but when they got there, he was already dead. His legs, arms, and knees were brown with bruises, and his head had a hole in it. The junta did not return Myo Linn's body to his family and instead cremated him themselves on January 7.
On January 7, a junta column raided Kyar Ta Kan Village, Kyunhla Township, Sagaing Region, and killed 58-year-old Tun Hla by burning him alive.

On January 10, children found an unexploded artillery shell that had been fired by junta forces and its militia in Wu Yang Village, Waingmaw Township, Kachin State. The children played with the shell, causing an explosion. As a result, 9-year-old Khaw Si lost his arm and was dead on arrival at the hospital. Two other children were also injured.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On January 12 at 2:30 p.m., a motorcycle coming from an industrial zone in Pakokku Township, Magway Region, was stopped for a check by the armed wing of the junta and Pyu Saw Htee personnel on Pakokku-Yesagyo Road. As a result, one of the two men riding on the motorcycle was shot dead on the spot, and the other man was dead on arrival at the hospital. The two men were Myat Lin Aung and Ye Lin Khet from Pakokku Myotthit.

On January 12 at 2:30 p.m., a motorcycle coming from an industrial zone in Pakokku Township, Magway Region, was stopped for a check by the armed wing of the junta and Pyu Saw Htee personnel on Pakokku-Yesagyo Road. The motorcycle was speeding over the limit and had trouble controlling its speed. The junta shot the motorcycle as it tried to brake at the checkpoint. As a result, one of the two men riding on the motorcycle was shot dead on the spot, and the other man was dead on arrival at the hospital. The two men were Myat Lin Aung and Ye Lin Khet from Pakokku Myotthit.

On September 7, 2022, Aung Zaw Min, owner of a guitar and eyeglasses shop in Myoma Ward, Letpadan Township, Bago Region, was arrested by the junta on accusation of him supporting the NUG and PDF. The junta took him to a jail cell at the Letpadan Police Station. He suffered serious injuries due to getting beaten and tortured during interrogation, and although he was treated at Letpadan Hospital, he did not get better. As a result, on October 13, he was treated at Thayarwady Hospital. On October 14, the Letpadan Police Station informed Aung Zaw Min's family of his death. When the family went to check his body, they were not allowed to check the body closely or take pictures of it. Although his family was allowed to cremate him on October 15, his body was delivered to the cemetery from the Letpandan Police Station at the last minute, and the family was forced to cremate the body immediately.

On December 11, 2022, while Imam Naing Soe (aka) MawLawi Ozyne who lived in Hpayarthonesu Town, Kayin State, was on his way to go shopping in Mudon Town, Mon State, he was arrested at the checkpoint of the junta’s Border Guard Forces (BGF) in Chaung Na Kwa Village, Kyainseikgyi Township, Kayin State, and then he was disappeared. One month later, his family reported that Naing Soe was killed in January. Although his family requested to get his body at the BGF checkpoint, his body was not returned. His motorcycle and 800,000 kyats were also not returned.

On January 14 at 4 p.m, university student Win Zaw Tun, who lived in Tha Yet Kone Village, Hla Pa Chin Village Tract, Nattalin Township, Bago Region, was going from Tha Yet Kone Village to Nattalin Town. He drove his motorcycle through the junta's checkpoint at the entrance of Kyot Lay Pin Village, Kone Thar Village Tract, Tar Pun Town. As a result, he was shot four times and killed by Kyaw Min Thu, a soldier who was at the checkpoint.

on January 3 at around 5 p.m., junta forces fired heavy weaponry into Lwe Htway Village, Loikaw Township, Kayah State, despite no clashes taking place. As a result, local villager Nan Mray died from injuries to her head, ribs, and hips by an artillery shell. Another woman was also injured.

on January 9 at 11 p.m., Ma Har Thi, age 17, was shot and killed by the 274 Infantry Battalion based in Mindat Township. She was killed at home in Li Laung Village, Mindat Township, Chin State. On January 7, Ma Har Thi’s father had been arrested and taken by the junta to perform forced labor. When her father ran away from the junta on January 9, the junta raided their house and fired shots, killing Ma Har Thi that night.

On January 16 at around 8 p.m., the junta’s 421 Artillery Battalion based in Pekon Township fired heavy weaponry into Kaung Saung Village, Mobye Town, Pekon Township, Shan State. The weaponry exploded in a shelter of Internally Displaced Persons (IDPs) in the village. The explosion killed Mu Lin, an IDP, and injured two men, also IDPs. Mu Lin had fled to Kaung Saung Village because of the war in Done Du Htan Village.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On January 9, the junta's LIB-364 and IB-701 forces raided and set fire to Chaung Nar Village, Tabayin Township, Sagaing Region. Then, they abducted Thein Tun and Myint Swe, who were locals of the village. On January 11, Thein Tun was found in Chaung Nar Village with serious, torture-inflicted injuries. On January 17, he died from those injuries. Myint Swe, who was arrested with him, was released.
He was shot in his hand and then arrested. He later died while in detention.

On the morning of January 18, around 70 personnel from an infantry battalion under Division 88 clashed with the PDFs and the All Burma Students' Democratic Front. The clash occurred about five miles from Moe Tar Lay Village, Katha Township, Sagaing Region. At around 6 p.m. that day, junta forces firebombed Moe Tar Lay Village with two fighter planes. As a result, seven locals died, and more than 30 people were injured. The deceased were Nyo, Tin Nyein, San Myint, Aye Khaing, Khin Mar Kyi, U U Htwe, and Maung Lwin – six female villagers and one man, respectively.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: Aung Myo Min, aka Min Min, was arrested, and he was charged with violating the Counter-Terrorism Law. He died on November 9, 2022, in Monywa Prison without having any particular disease.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ရဲဝင်းအောင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On January 20, a junta column with over 130 personnel attacked Lel Mhee Village, Tigyaing Township, Sagaing Region. The junta took away three locals: Ye Win Aung, Nyo Aye, and San Wai. On the morning of January 21, their bodies were discovered in a forest near U Shit Kone Village, Indaw Township, Sagaing Region.

On January 20, a junta column with over 130 personnel attacked Lel Mhee Village, Tigyaing Township, Sagaing Region. The junta took away three locals: Ye Win Aung, Nyo Aye, and San Wai. On the morning of January 21, their bodies were discovered in a forest near U Shit Kone Village, Indaw Township, Sagaing Region.

On January 20, a junta column with over 130 personnel attacked Lel Mhee Village, Tigyaing Township, Sagaing Region. The junta took away three locals: Ye Win Aung, Nyo Aye, and San Wai. On the morning of January 21, their bodies were discovered in a forest near U Shit Kone Village, Indaw Township, Sagaing Region.

On the morning of October 16, 2022, the junta arrested Lu Lu Ko, aka Phoe Thar, a member of the People's Defence Force, at his house in Dagon Myothit (Seikkan) Township, Yangon Region. His house was seized that evening, and property inside the house was taken away. Lu Lu Ko died at Shwepyithar Interrogation Center on November 2, 2022.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: သန်းကြွယ်သူ (ခ) ဟာရှင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 5, urban guerrillas attacked a checkpoint gate at the entrance of Monywa Town, Sagaing Region. While withdrawing, urban guerrilla Than Kywal Thu, aka Har Shin, was injured. He was arrested by the junta forces at a village. On December 6, he was killed, and his head was hung at the entrance gate of Monywa Town.
In November, a junta column raided Kyay Mhone Village, Mone Yay Village Tract, Monywa Township, Sagaing Region, and arrested local Kyaw Myo Wai. Two days later, his family was informed of his death.

Junta forces attacked villages near the Letpadaung Copper Mine in Salingyi Township, Sagaing Region. On the afternoon of January 14, the junta arrested Khaing Soe of Kyauk Phyu Tai Village. On January 19, his body was discovered in a palm forest to the east of Shwe Hlay Village, five miles from Kyauk Phyu Tai Village.

On January 21 at around 1:30 p.m., junta forces attacked a rural hospital in Ba Hin Village, Myaing Township, Magway Region, with an Mi-35 helicopter. As a result, Kyi, a patient's caretaker, lost her leg and died from blood loss. She was hiding under a tamarind tree during the attack.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: လင်းလင်းဝေ (ခ) ဘူး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On January 17, junta forces entered Shat Pon Village, Myeik District, Palaw Township, Tanintharyi Region. Lin Lin Wai, aka Buu, ran into the junta forces while going to work. The junta forces slit his throat. Lin Lin Wai died from the injury.

On January 20 at 6 p.m., junta forces shot and killed Loon Khin, who was from Pala Town, Palaw Township, Myeik District, Tanintharyi Region. He was shot dead while returning to his house on his motorbike. His house was located in front of Pala Police Station. His body and motorbike were not returned to his family.
On January 19 and 20, junta forces with around 150 personnel attacked Ye-U Township, Sagaing Region. On January 19, Aung Soe of Tu Maung Village ran into the junta and was shot dead in the head.

In August 2022, junta forces searched for and arrested people working as metal welders in Industrial Zone Ward, Monywa Town, Sagaing Region. The junta arrested Tin Moe Win, aka Moe Gyi. His body was recovered within 24 hours after his arrest, and it had been operated on.

In August 2022, junta forces searched for and arrested people working as metal welders in Industrial Zone Ward, Monywa Town, Sagaing Region. The junta arrested Aye Min Thant, aka Aye Gyi. His body was recovered within 24 hours after his arrest, and it had been operated on.

In May, a gunpowder explosion took place at Htan Daw Ward, Monywa Town, Sagaing Region, and the junta forces arrested Toe Aung (aka) Tut Pi, who was injured by the explosion. The following day Toe Aung's family retrieved his body covered with stitches from Monywa Mortuary.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ထွန်းထွန်းဝင်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: Accused of contacting the Salingyi People’s Defence Force, Tun Tun Win was arrested in October 2022. Afterwards, he died at the interrogation center. His family was not able to retrieve his body.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ရဲလင်းအောင် (ခ) ဂျပန်ကြီး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: Accused of contacting the Salingyi People’s Defence Force, Ye Linn Aung, aka Japan Gyi, was arrested in October 2022. Afterwards, he died at the interrogation center. His family was not able to retrieve his body.

In September 2022, Min Thu Zaw, aka Arr Noe, was arrested at his house in Htan Daw Ward, Monywa Town, Sagaing Region. A month and a half after his arrest, the junta forces transported him to Monywa Hospital. He died about a week after that.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: သက်ပိုင်စိုး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On August 24, Thet Paing Soe was arrested by junta forces who were unable to find his friend while visiting his friend's house briefly. He was killed because he did not say anything when he was asked about his friend. On August 25, his body, which had signs of being operated on, was returned to his family with the explanation that he died from COVID-19.
Ko Ko Naing, aka Naing Gyi, was arrested on January 3, 2022, and died on November 5. He was from Monywa Town, Sagaing Region.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldHfL2UA8oU0Imne: Aung Myo Zaw (aka) Ko Ngal Lay
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: Aung Myo Zaw, (aka) Ko Ngal Lay, was arrested. He died on July 1. He was from Myawaddy Ward, Monywa Town, Sagaing Region.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: နေမင်းခ (ခ) ဗိုလ်ကြီး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: Nay Min Kha, aka Bol Gyi, was arrested on May 1, 2022, and died on May 3. He was from Myawaddy Ward, Monywa Town, Sagaing Region.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အောင်မြင့်မြတ်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On August 16, Aung Myint Myat was arrested in Monywa Town. Junta forces made him show the location of his friends' base, and he showed them the wrong locations. As a result, he was tortured, and on August 18, he was killed. He was from Myawaddy Ward, Monywa Town, Sagaing Region.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: နိုင်နိုင်ဝင်း

On the night of August 27, 2022, around 50 junta personnel came to the house of the parents of Ye Htut, and arrested Ye Htut by beating him. Afterwards, they showed Ye Htut the papers they brought with them and told him to lead them to the people in the papers. On August 28, his body was discovered somewhere in a former jungle base near the village. Ye Htut was from Ywar Ton Village, Monywa Town, Sagaing Region.

On the morning of January 21, a Pyu Saw Htee leader from Lon Taung Village, Madaya Township, Mandalay Region, was killed. Afterwards, junta forces arrested three youth PDF members. Two of the PDF members were from Lon Taung Village, and Din Gyi, the other PDF member, was from Kyone Village. Afterwards, the three of them were killed, and their bodies were kept at Madaya Town Mortuary. On the morning of January 22, the junta informed the village administrator to retrieve the bodies.

He was living in Than Pa Yar Pin Yoe cluster in the northern part of Sone Chaung Village.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On January 23 in Tamu Township, Sagaing Region, three youth traveling from Kyun Pin Thar Village to Tamu Town were interrogated by the junta in front of a military camp in Koon Taung Village. The junta arrested them, accusing them of contacting the People’s Defence Force, and killed them. Those three youth were Let Ming Thang from Kyun Pin Thar Village, Shwe Ming Thang and Ngam Ming Hau, age 17, both from Myot Ma 14 Section in Chaung Natt Gyi Village. The junta did not return their dead bodies to their families.

The junta arrested them, accusing them of contacting the People’s Defence Force, and killed them. Those three youth were Let Ming Thang from Kyun Pin Thar Village, Shwe Ming Thang and Ngam Ming Hau, age 17, both from Myot Ma 14 Section in Chaung Natt Gyi Village. The junta did not return their dead bodies to their families.

On January 24, a clash broke out between the People’s Defence Force and the junta in Tanintharyi Township, Tanintharyi Region. Afterwards, the junta indiscriminately fired heavy weaponry into nearby villages, killing Thein Khin, age 90, from Ou Yin Kan Village.

On January 25, more than 100 junta personnel raided Ma Kyi Kone Village, Thabeikkyin Township, Mandalay Region. The junta arrested and killed villager Min Maung. They also arrested Min Maung’s wife, 16-year-old son, and 10-year-old daughter.

On January 26, junta forces attacked Si Laung and Aung Chan Thar Villages, Yinmarbin Township, Sagaing Region. While the locals were seeking refuge, Si Laung villager Zaw Win Tun ran into the junta forces in the village and was arrested. His body was discovered by locals on January 28.

Kyaw Zin Latt, aka Shangyi, was a motorbike taxi driver from Saik Ka Lay Su Taw Village, Shwegyin Township, Bago Region. On January 22, after Kyaw Zin Latt took a taxi passenger to Theinzayat Town, Mon State, the owner of a betel shop located across from the base of Infantry Battalion 207 (IB-207) accused him of taking her husband to the PDF. This accusation led to his arrest by a battalion commander of IB-207 who was sitting in the shop. Kyaw Zin Latt was sent to an interrogation center. While being detained, he was not allowed to see his family members, and on January 25, the Theinzayat Funeral Society returned his body with serious injuries to his family.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: မေစန္ဒီလင်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On January 26 at around 2 p.m., an artillery shell fired by junta forces in Paw Ma Myaing Village, Katha Township, Sagaing Region, exploded on a house in Kyauk Hton Gyi Village. May Sandi Lin, age 12, was injured in the head and died on the spot. Moreover, her brother Phyo Thu Lin, age 14, was injured.

Htin Kyaw was living with his wife and son in Bayinnaung, Yangon City. He went to stay in Aung San Ward, Natmauk Town, Magway Region, to look after his sick mother. On April 29, 2022, he posted on Facebook about junta soldiers who died while raiding a PDF base in Natmauk Township. As a result, junta soldiers and police arrested him at home in Natmauk Town on April 30, and killed him that night.

On October 18, 2022, junta soldiers and police arrested civilian Aung Kyaw Kyaw, who was residing in Myoma Kwet Thit Ward, Natmauk Town, Magway Region. He was killed that night at Natmauk Police Station.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On September 17, 2022, junta forces attacked Aung Chan Thar Village, In Koke Kar Village Tract, Taze Township, Sagaing Region. The junta shot and killed Maung Maung, who was mentally unwell. The junta burned his body along with his clothes.
On January 25, the junta attacked Khin Mon Village, Chaung-U Township, Sagaing Region. During the attack, local Pauk Si ran into a junta column and was shot dead after being captured.

On January 27 at around 8 a.m., without a battle taking place, the junta's Hopin Town-based Infantry Battalion 40 fired heavy weaponry indiscriminately into Nant Yin Village, Hopin Town, Kachin State. As a result, Mi Kyi and her son Sai Sai were struck by an artillery shell while going to the fields. The artillery shell killed Sai Sai on the spot and injured Mi Kyi, who received treatment at Myitkyina Hospital.

On the afternoon of January 20, junta forces bombed a PDF base in Mogoke Township, Mandalay Region, with three planes. As a result, Pub G, a column commander of the PDF's 1222 Battalion, died, and three PDF members were seriously injured.

On December 22, around 80 personnel in a junta column fired at Aung Chan Thar Village, Mawlaik Township, Sagaing Region with various weaponry and raided it. During the process, Win Myint was hit by the weaponry and died.

On January 29, junta forces raided Maubin East Village, Shwebo Township, Sagaing Region, and set houses on fire. The junta also killed two villagers, Myint Than and Kan Htoo, and burnt their bodies. On the morning of January 30, the locals found their bodies after the junta left the village.

On January 29, junta forces raided Maubin East Village, Shwebo Township, Sagaing Region, and set houses on fire. The junta also killed two villagers, Myint Than and Kan Htoo, and burnt their bodies. On the morning of January 30, the locals found their bodies after the junta left the village.

on January 30 at 8 p.m., in Ngwe Twin Village, Ayadaw Township, Sagaing Region, junta forces and the local Pyu Saw Htee arrested three villagers for questioning. Those villagers were Zaw Naing, Kyaw Min Soe, and Shit Bot. On January 31, the junta told Kyaw Min Soe’s family members to come and pick up his body. The condition of the other two locals is still unknown.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: on January 27, the junta attacked Kokko Kone Village, Kawlin Township, Sagaing Region, with two fighter aircrafts. During the attack, the junta shot local Khaing Zin Nwe in the head, killing her on the spot.

On January 30 at 8 a.m., a family from Yin Yain Village, Kani Township, Sagaing Region, was returning to Kani Township from Yinmarbin Township by motorized canoe. At that time, a junta boat fired shots near Tha Pyay Taw Village, Kani Township. As a result, one of the family members, Mar Mar Win, died of a heart attack. She suffered from a heart disease before she died.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On February 25, 2022, at around 1 p.m., junta soldiers and Pyu Saw Htee members from Inn Koke Kar Village opened fire and raided Chaung Sone (South) Village, Taze Township, Sagaing Region. A local named Nay Win tried to run away, but he got shot him in the thigh and hid in a haystack nearby. When the Pyu Saw Htee members found him hiding, they killed him by setting the haystack on fire.

Kyaw Tint, a resident of No. 5 Ward, Chauk Township, Magway Region, was accused of financially supporting the Chauk People’s Defence Force. Junta forces from Infantry Battalion 13 (IB-13) arrested Kyaw Tint on February 1. The junta interrogated him at the IB-13 base. He died on the morning of February 2. The junta did not inform his family about his death.

On February 1, the junta raided and indiscriminately fired both heavy and light weaponry into Nyaung Pin Thar Village, Kawlin Township, Sagaing Region. During the raid, the junta shot Zaw Min Khaing and injured three other villagers.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On the afternoon of February 1, the junta fired heavy weaponry from a traditional medicine hospital in Ye-U Township into Muu Thar Kone Village, Ye-U Township, Sagaing Region. The weaponry exploded on a house in the village, hitting and killing a 20-year-old woman.

On February 3, junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee members raided Min Yat Village, Launglon Township, Tanintharyi Region. During the raid, they shot villager Tin Laung dead and then set his house on fire. Later that day, Tin Laung's body was discovered among the banana trees next to his house.

On February 3 at around 6 p.m., junta forces fired an artillery shell at Tan Shin Village, Palaw Township, Tanintharyi Region. The shell exploded on a house in the village, killing a woman named Than Maw on the spot and injuring a child. They were both in the house at the time.

On February 2 at around 9 a.m., around 30 junta personnel opened fire on and raided Ta Tar Oo Village, Sagaing Township, Sagaing Region. During the raid, the junta killed Linn Yupar Myo, age 6, by shooting her in the stomach. Additionally, more than 60 houses in the village were set on fire.

On June 1 at around 1 p.m., a Pyu Saw Htee group from Khun Taung Gyi Village, Shwebo Township, attacked a lookout post in Shwebo Township guarded by four members of the Farmer's Independence Force (FIF). After they captured the four FIF members, the Pyu Saw Htee group tied their hands behind their backs and shot them in the head, killing them on the spot. The FIF members included Naing Tun Oo, aka Shwe Kyar.

On the night of July 31, a Pyu Saw Htee group killed Nyi Nyi by smashing his head near Shwe Pwint Phyu Yard located in In Daing Village, Tamu Township, Sagaing Region. At the time, Nyi Nyi was returning home from Tamu Town after selling the chili he bought from In Daing Village. His body was discovered on August 1 around 5 p.m. Nyi Nyi was from Pan Thar Village, which is known for the many Pyu Saw Htee members residing there. He had been seeking refuge in In Daing Village.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: မြင့်မောင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On July 31 at around 12 p.m., Pyu Saw Htee members captured Myint Maung, who was from Myoma 12/b Ward, Tamu Town, Sagaing Region. They took him to Jone San Paan Shop in the ward. At around 4 p.m., they shot him dead near Per Hel Chaung Bridge. Myint Maung was working as a simple carpenter.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အောင်ဆန်းလင်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 29 at around 5 p.m., Aung San Linn was returning from Moe Ray Town when a Pyu Saw Htee group pulled his motorcycle over for inspection. They shot him dead near No. 14 Bridge after accusing him of contacting the PDF and arresting him. His body was discovered near Nang Phalong Ward on the afternoon of November 2, and his body was delivered by Nate Ban Lan Funeral Service. Aung San Linn was from Saw Bwar Ward, Tamu Town, Sagaing Region.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ချစ်စမ်းမောင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 31 at around 7 p.m., a Pyu Saw Htee group led by Pan Chi Chan Myay shot Chit San Maung and his wife dead at their tea shop in Nang Phalong, Myoma Ward, Tamu Town. The couple died on the spot, and their son was injured in his arm and ribs.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On December 31 at around 7 p.m., a Pyu Saw Htee group led by Pan Chi Chan Myay shot Chit San Maung and his wife dead at their tea shop in Nang Phalong, Myoma Ward, Tamu Town. The couple died on the spot, and their son was injured in his arm and ribs.

On February 19, Nandar was accused of assisting police Zaw Linn Aung from Thayet Myoma Police Station in joining CDM. Nandar was a construction aggregate shop owner from Kyan Seint Kyi Village, Myaing Township, Magway Region. Thayet Myoma Police Station and Division 101 arrested her and decapitated her after questioning.

cellValuesByColumnId.fld7KLBHB6DdATjnu: U Hla Myint + Daw Khin Yee Ma
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: In Sagaing Region, locals had to flee for safety because of a battle in Shwe Pyi Aye Town, Homalin Township, from February 1 to February 4. On the evening of February 4, junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee members shot and killed Zin Min Htut, Lecturer in Oriental Studies from Monywa University, when he was returning to check on his house.

On the morning of February 7, around 20 junta personnel captured Paing Soe and Phyo Ngal Zaw, two local villagers working at a rubber plantation in Ya Nge Village, Thayetchaung Township, Tanintharyi Region.  They were captured whilst inside the house at the plantation. The junta forces tied them up and shot them dead in a yard by the street.

On the morning of February 7, around 20 junta personnel captured Paing Soe and Phyo Ngal Zaw, two local villagers working at a rubber plantation in Ya Nge Village, Thayetchaung Township, Tanintharyi Region.  They were captured whilst inside the house at the plantation. The junta forces tied them up and shot them dead in a yard by the street.

on February 5, a Pyu Saw Htee pro-junta militia from Kywal Pon Village arrested Paw Htay. After arrest, the Pyu Saw Htee personnel questioned and killed him. His body was found in a mango grove near Kywal Pone Village on February 7. Paw Htay was from Yin Ma Kyin Village in Sagaing Township, Sagaing Region.

At 9 a.m. on December 6, 2022, the junta arrested Kyaw Zayar Phyo, aka Zayar, while he was working at the goldsmith place at the market in Zigon Township, Bago Region. The junta accused him of supporting the People’s Defence Force. After his arrest, he was interrogated at the Zigon Township police station by Military Security Affairs personnel from Nattalin District. Kyaw Zayar Phyo died at the Zigon Township General Hospital on December 16, 2022.  At the time of his death, he had been receiving medical treatment for two days because of his injuries from being severely tortured during interrogation.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On the evening of November 12, a Pyu Saw Htee militia, led by Thida Yu Mon and operating under the name “Blood Comrades,” came to arrest Myo Kyaw at Pan Gangaw Tea Shop in No. 5 Ward of Natogyi Town, Myingyan District, Mandalay Region. Myo Kyaw is the owner of the tea shop. However, the group was unable to find him, so the group abducted two waiters, covering the waiters' faces with cloth. On the morning of November 13, their bodies were discovered to the west of Natogyi Town. They were killed by gunshot, and their bodies showed knife wounds.

The junta also arrested two men from Htan Gwa Village, Natogyi Township: Kyaw Min and Zin Min. One of the bodies was discovered to the west of Natogyi Town at a monastery's visitor hall, and the other four bodies were discovered at the intersection of Natogyi-Myittha Road and the road leading to Htan Gwa Village.

On the night of October 3, 2022, junta forces arrested NLD member Tun Zaw in his house. The next day they disposed of his body. His body was discovered with a "Kyaukpadaung Blood Brother group" calling card attached.

On the morning of October 2, 2022, Pyu Saw Htee and Blood Brother members arrested NLD Nyaung-U District Kyaw Win and his daughter from Sel VIllage, Ngathayauk Town, Nyaung-U Township. Then they let the daughter go. Afterwards, they killed Kyaw Win. The next day, they disposed of his body near a garbage pileup in Sel Village. Kyaw Win had been evading arrest and was killed when he returned home to Sel Village.

Junta forces arrested Phone Myint Moe, aka Moe Gyi, in a beer bar on the evening of April 25, 2022. On the morning of April 27, his body was disposed of near Thingazar Stream on 26th Street in Mandalay Town. He was the brother of Zaw Zaw Aung, the People's Hluttaw Representative of Mahaaungmyay Township, Mandalay Region.

Members of Blood Brother and Pyu Saw Htee intended to arrest NLD Ward and Village Chairman Min Min Zaw in Pauk Kone Ward, Mingaladon Township. They wanted to arrest him for leading the efforts to eliminate junta informants and bomb junta offices in Mingaladon Township. However, Blood Brothers and Pyu Saw Htee were unable to find him after three attempts. As a result, on October 7, 2022, they abducted Min Min Zaw's father Saw Naing. They shot him dead at a bus stop in front of the Pyin Ma Pin Milk Factory.

On July 25, at around 12:30 a.m., Pwar from Tha Bawt Seik Village, Launglon Township, Tanintharyi Region, was accused of supporting PDFs. She was arrested in her house by members of military intelligence, police, Kite Force, and Pyu Saw Htee. She was then shot dead.

On July 25 at around 1:30 a.m., Zaw Win from Maungmagan Village, Launglon Township, Tanintharyi Region, was arrested in his house by members of military intelligence, police, Kite Force and Pyu Saw Htee. He was accused of supporting PDFs. He was taken outside his house and then was killed by being shot in the head and arms. They also took two rings, two phones, and a car from his house.

On the morning of February 6, a Pyu Saw Htee group from Kywal Pon Village, Sagaing Township, Sagaing Region, shot Win Aung while he was working in a mango grove near Kywal Pon Village. His body was found in a mango grove near Kywal Pon Village on February 7. Win Aung was from San Thit Village, Sagaing Township, Sagaing Region.

on February 9 at around 6 p.m., junta forces shot local Bee Lo Htan, (aka Bee Bee), in Taung Zalat Ward, Kale Township, Sagaing Region. They shot him in the head, killing him on the spot. The junta forces had been stationed at the Travel Audit Office in the ward. At the time of his death, Bee Lo Htan was sitting near a bridge on Anawyahtar Road, which is close to the Travel Audit Office.

On February 7, after a clash broke out between Karen National Liberation Army (KNLA) and around 50 junta personnel near Ohm Pin Su Village, Kyaukkyi Township, Bago Region, junta forces fired heavy weaponry into the village from Nat Than Kwin Bridge at around 11:20 p.m. that night. This resulted in the death of Saw Gyar Luu who got hit with an artillery shell. Three other people were injured.

On February 8 at around 10 p.m., personnel at the Mel Zar Police Station shot Soe Naing dead while he was walking back from Mel Zar Village to A Lel Sate Village in Indaw Township, Sagaing Region. Soe Naing was a resident of Lel Sate Village and suffered from mental illness.

Because of the explosion, a novice monk in front of the monastery died, and a 60-year-old monk sustained arm and back injuries.

On February 13, junta forces raided the house where his funeral was being held. The junta arrested the people in attendance including his family members. As well as seizing the dead body of Di Par without allowing him to be cremated, under the pretense of needing to do an autopsy on the body.

A local of To Village called Soe Pu was seeking refuge in a nearby village of Palaw Township, Tanintharyi Region. On February 13 at around 11 a.m., junta forces stationed on the village mountain shot Soe Pu dead while he was entering the village.

Kyi Win was burned alive, as he was bedridden because of sickness. Phoe Kyaw, who had a leg disability, was detained and had his hands tied behind his back and was later killed from a blade wound to his neck.

On November 26, after entering Mauk Lin Village in Gangaw Township, Magway Region, around 100 junta personnel arrested and tortured five cowherds. On November 27, Thar Tun, one of the cowherds, was killed. Then, while using the remaining four cowherds as human shields, the junta personnel arrested five internally displaced people (IDPs) in the village's IDP tents. Then, the junta let the four cowherds go. On November 28, four of the five IDPs were killed at Taung Ta Lote Le Kwe-Ywar Myin Hill. Their names were Hla Saung, Tin Maung Win, Naung Naung, and Hmine Wai.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: မေဇွန်မိုး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On January 29, the junta arrested May Zun Moe at their Tain Nyunt Checkpoint near Kyauk Phyu Taung Village, Aye Mya Thar Yar Village Tract, in Okpho Township, Bago Region. May Zun Moe was a nurse who joined the Civil Disobedience Movement. She was arrested while returning to Okpho Town after delivering a baby. After arresting her, the junta interrogated her at an interrogation center. On February 16, the junta shot her dead and set her body on fire. It was reported that she was raped before being killed; this has not been independently confirmed yet. On February 16, her body was discovered at the edge of a jungle near Htan Pin Kone Village.

On February 28, around 80 junta personnel attacked Bo Tae Village in Wetlet Township, Sagaing Region, and set 2 houses on fire. As a result, 70-year-old Tin Hla burned alive in one of the houses because she could not flee the attack.

At around 8 a.m. the next day, as the junta forces were leaving the village, they encountered Myint Than on the outskirts of the village and shot him dead. At the time of his death, Myint Than was returning by motorbike to Mote Soe Chan Butar Village, where he resided.

On the evening of March 1, a column of junta forces attacked Tar Tai Village in Sagaing Township, Sagaing Region. On the morning of March 2, while leaving the village, the junta column took three women and 13 men as human shields. According to the statement from the locals, 3 women were raped and killed. The junta killed them on a road and then left their bodies there. To prevent the bodies from being recovered, the junta planted bombs and mines under the bodies.

On March 21, junta forces raided and set fire to Aout Kyauk Wut Village in Launglon Township, Tanintharyi Region; burning to ash around 40 houses. Junta troops also shot Kham Mae in the head dead. His body was discovered when the junta forces had left the village in the evening.

cellValuesByColumnId.fld7KLBHB6DdATjnu: U Ba San + Daw Sein Pow
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On March 19, around 100 junta personnel raided Mee Laung Kyun Village in Yae Lel Kyun Area, Yesagyo Township, Magway Region, and shot dead 2 locals. The junta forces killed Maung Han mentally-unwell Myat Soe on March 20. On March 21, the junta forces left the village and two of their bodies were discovered in the village.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: မြတ်စိုးဦး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On March 19, around 100 junta personnel raided Mee Laung Kyun Village in Yae Lel Kyun Area, Yesagyo Township, Magway Region, and shot dead 2 locals. The junta forces killed Maung Han on March 19 and killed mentally-unwell Myat Soe  on March 20. On March 21, the junta forces left the village and two of their bodies were discovered in the village.

In the morning of March 21, junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee militiamen, stationed in Zee Phyu Kone Village, Pale Township in Sagaing Region, clashed with the People’s Defence Force (PDF). In the ensuing clash, junta forces fired heavy weaponry and then, an attack helicopter arrived and opened fire. As a result, Khin Win from Thayet Village was killed when she was hit with a heavy weaponry shrapnel.

On March 20, junta forces fired heavy weaponry at Htoo Maw Dae (West) Village in Baw Thay Htar Village Tract, Hpapun Township, Kayin State. As a result, a local named Saw A Bo was immediately killed when hit with a shrapnel to the stomach.

On March 23, at around 8 a.m.,around 60 junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee militiamen raided Mya Kan Village in Khin-U Township, Sagaing Region, and set fire to the village. They detained and killed 65-year-old Nyo Tin after torturing him. His body was discovered in front of his house after the junta forces left around 10 a.m. that day.

On March 24, when junta forces raided Palaw Kone Village in Palaw Township, Tanintharyi Region, a clash ensued with the local PDFs. Then on March 25, junta forces detained and killed Tin Oo, a local villager. Moreover, Nat Eain Taung Village local Myo Min Thu ran into the junta forces seeking refuge and was shot dead.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On March 23, at around 4 p.m, approximately 150 junta personnel raided Nyaung Zin Gyi Village in Htan Kone Rural Area, Kanbalu Township, Sagaing Region. Junta troops then burned alive and killed mentally-unwell Tun Min Oo. They also set fire to 32 houses, 17 motorbikes, along with farming equipment and grain.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: In the morning of March 22, an artillery shell fired by BGF stationed in Hpa-An Township, Kayin State, exploded in Tatar Oo Village, Hpa-An Township, killing a Buddhist nun. Moreover, at around 11 p.m. that day, junta forces carried out bombings with two fighter planes, killing a villager from Lar Chae Chaw Village in the explosion.

On March 22, at around 7 a.m., around 70 junta personnel raided Pwint Hlyat Village in Mingin Township, Sagaing Region, and set fire to the houses. They also shot dead Tin who was trapped in his house, with his body discovered on March 22 with bullet wounds.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: သက်ပိုင်စိုး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On March 8 and 9, the junta arrested eight locals from Zee Kone Town in Kanbalu Township, Sagaing Region. Six of the detainees were released; some on March 10, and some on March 16. Two of the locals, Thet Paing Soe and Chit Min Naing, were kept in detainment. On March 24, their bodies were discovered with stab wounds in a ditch outside of Zee Kone Town. Although their families asked for their deceased loved ones to be buried in accordance to Islamic tradition, the junta did not allow it.

cellValuesByColumnId.fld7KLBHB6DdATjnu: Saw Myint Oo + Naw Ma Taw
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On March 24, at around 11 a.m., the No. 8 Infantry Battalion shot villagers Saw Nga Pyuu and Saw Ye Naing Win dead, while the Battalion was on hidden watch near Daukyat Village in Bilin Township, Mon State. The Battalion shot the two villagers for no apparent reason while they were walking. The villagers died on the spot.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: သန်းလင်းချစ်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On March 25, at around 1 p.m., while two men on a motorbike were passing a junta checkpoint in Ka Ma Hlaing Village, Tanintharyi Township, Tanintharyi Region, a junta personnel shot at them for allegedly being PDF members. As a result, Than Linn Chit, who was riding on the backseat, fell off the bike from getting shot and died on the spot. Pyae Sone Aung (aka A Linn Yaung), who was driving the motorbike, was also shot; he drove to a clinic in Pa Wa Village and died while seeking treatment there.

On March 27, at around 12 p.m., junta forces fired heavy weaponry in Mae Yone Lay Village, Kyaikto Township, Mon State, despite no clash taking place. One of the artillery shells exploded in a plantation field in the village, instantly killing local gardener Saw Naung Oo as he was working in the field. Six other local gardeners were injured. The six were sent to Kyaikto Township Hospital for treatment; Zaw Htet Aung (aka) Thar Chaung, one of the six, died at the hospital while being treated.

On March 25, at around 8 a.m., around 50 junta personnel raided and set fire to Sone Kone Village in Budalin Township, Sagaing Region. As a result, a visually-impaired person and six other ill locals were burned alive, as they were unable to flee. Around 180 houses were burned down. The seven deceased individuals were Kyi Myint (aka Japan Gyi), Khway Ma, Khin Myint, and Tin Ei, all in their eighties; Pyae and Kyi Aung, both age 75; and San Myint, age 50.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On January 9, around 150 personnel, including members of the junta's No. 368 Light Infantry Battalion and Pyu Saw Htee coalition forces, raided Tal Pin and Shan Kone Villages in Kanbalu  Township, Sagaing Region, and arrested 3 locals seeking refuge as hostages. Then the personnel killed them and set them on fire. The deceased were Khin Maung Tun from Shan Kone Village, and two brothers, Kyaw Soe Moe and San Myint Aung, from Tal Pin Village. On January 10 and 11, their bodies were discovered near Tal Pin Village.

On the morning of March 30, around 68 junta personnel raided and attacked Myaung Township, Sagaing Region. They captured Wai Phyo Hlyan (aka Sin Yine), a deputy battalion commander of PDF Sagaing District Battalion No. 1, and decapitated him alive. His head was taken by the junta forces, and his body was recovered at around 10 a.m.

On March 30, the junta's No. 33 Light Infantry Battalion abducted four civilians, including two children under the age of 18, from Maung Htaung Village in Sagaing Township, Sagaing Region. Later, all four civilians were killed. The deceased were Kyaw Thu Tun, O-Ei, Ton Ton Chit, and Chit Suu. Their bodies were discovered at Nyaung Pin Wun Bridge on March 31 and April 1.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On March 30, at around 1 p.m., junta forces pulled over a vehicle at a checkpoint near Kamaing Town. The vehicle was carrying rice and motor oil from Mogaung Town, Kachin State. The junta forces accused the people of being members of the PDF, shooting one man dead while arresting another person. The deceased was Mite Mite from Hmaw Wan Ward in Hpakant Township. His body was not returned to his family, and the junta forces in Kamaing took his body to a strategic hill.

Among the injured was Salai Van Cem Lian, who died on April 1 after suffering serious injuries.

On the evening of March 31, junta forces bombed U La Ba Pagoda between Wae Gyi and Inn Daung Villages in Tigyaing Township, Sagaing Region, where the internally displaced people were located. The junta used fighter planes for the bombing, which killed six locals and injured five locals. The deceased include Soe Naing, Nyo Nwet, Aung Paing, and Mar Lar Moe, all from Wae Gyi Village. The other two deceased individuals have yet to be identified.

On April 1, around 80 junta personnel raided the area near Letpadaung Mountain Copper Mine in Salingyi Township, Sagaing Region. The junta forces shot Toe Gyi dead and arrested Naing. Then on April 3, Naing's body was discovered in a field one mile away from Kan Kone Village. His body had injuries from being tortured. Both Toe Gyi and Naing were locals of Kan Kone Village.

One of the artillery shells exploded on a house in the village. Artillery shrapnel hit 72-year-old Naw Swe Than in the head, killing her instantly. Four other locals were injured.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဝေသာလီထွန်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 3, at around 8 a.m., junta forces opened fire indiscriminately at Ma Ni Kone Village in Kyondoe Town, Kawkareik Township, Kayin State. As a result, 12-year-old Wai Tharli Tun was shot in the thigh while he was at a motorbike repair shop. He died while being transported to the hospital.

On April 3, at around 3 p.m, the junta's No. 257 Infantry Battalion fired heavy weaponry indiscriminately at the southern ward of Tharsi Village in Yesagyo Township, Magway Region. As a result, local Nay Zaw Phyo was killed by artillery shrapnel, and seven others were injured.

On March 31, around 150 junta personnel raided Bike Thayet Village in Salingyi Township, Sagaing Region. The junta personnel arrested Aye Ko, a local of Myin Nyar Bwar Village. Then on April 1, the junta forces left Bike Thayet Village, where Aye Ko's body was discovered with his hands tied behind his back.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အောင်နိုင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 4, at around 6 a.m., junta forces took five locals as hostages from Yin Taw Village in Wetlet Township, Sagaing Region. The junta detained the five locals at Hbone Bwet Village Monastery. While trying to free the hostages, GZ Special Task Force, a local defense force clashed with the junta forces between Saing Naing Lay Village and Hbone Bwet Village. Because the junta forces had more strength than the GZ Special Task Force, four GZ Special Task Force members were killed during the clash: Aung Naing from Bin Tae Kone Village, Kyi Khaing from Sa Kan Thar Village, Ye Min Htay from Saing Naing Gyi Village, and Linn Aung from Set Tan Gyi Village. Additionally, the junta forces captured GZ Special Task Force members Yan Naing Soe, from Yin Taw Village, and Thurain Htet. The junta shot them in the head, killing them.

On April 4, at around 6 a.m., junta forces took five locals as hostages from Yin Taw Village in Wetlet Township, Sagaing Region. The junta detained the five locals at Hbone Bwet Village Monastery. While trying to free the hostages, GZ Special Task Force, a local defense force clashed with the junta forces between Saing Naing Lay Village and Hbone Bwet Village. Because the junta forces had more strength than the GZ Special Task Force, four GZ Special Task Force members were killed during the clash: Aung Naing from Bin Tae Kone Village, Kyi Khaing from Sa Kan Thar Village, Ye Min Htay from Saing Naing Gyi Village, and Linn Aung from Set Tan Gyi Village. Additionally, the junta forces captured GZ Special Task Force members Yan Naing Soe, from Yin Taw Village, and Thurain Htet. The junta shot them in the head, killing them.

On April 3 and 4, around 100 junta personnel raided and set fire to Inn Lel Gyi Village in Kanbalu Township, Sagaing Region. Then the personnel killed two locals: Wa Li and Htay Maung. On April 4, the body of Wa Li was discovered in the village with a gunshot wound; Wa Li had suffered from a mental illness. On April 5, the burnt body of Htay Maung, with his hands tied behind his back, was found in the village.

Junta forces arrested Tun Linn from Amarapura Township, Mandalay Region, and he was sentenced to three years in prison under Penal Code Section 505 A. On the morning of March 30, 2023, Tun Linn, who was detained in Cell No. 6, Ward No. 3, of Obo Prison, died of a heart attack.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: စိုင်းဝါဝါထွန်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 5, at around 4 p.m., a clash broke out between junta forces and People's Defence Forces near Than Bo Village in Nawnghkio Township, Shan State. An artillery shell fired by junta forces exploded on a house in the village, killing 11-month-old Sai War War Tun and his 14-year-old sister Nang Ma Aye. Their parents were also seriously injured and are being treated at Pyinoolwin Hospital.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 5, a clash broke out between the People's Defence Force and around 85 junta personnel traveling on three trucks near Ar Yone Oo Village in Thabeikkyin Township, Mandalay Region. The junta forces opened fire indiscriminately, and as a result, a woman from Let Pan Kone Village was shot in the neck and died on the spot.

"On April 5, at around 1 p.m., Kyaw San was arrested after running into a military column of around 70 junta personnel. The junta tortured him and then killed him by shooting him in the head. Kyaw San was from Bae Pit Taw Village, Chaung-U Township, Sagaing Region. Before his death, he was supplying rations to the People’s Defence Force. "

On April 6, at around 4 p.m., Aung Ko from Zar Di Village Tract in Yebyu Township, Tanintharyi Region, was returning from the rubber plantations on a motorbike. When he arrived on Zar De-Khaung Pyan Street, he encountered three junta vehicles and was shot at before being arrested and taken away. On the morning of April 7, the junta forces returned his body, along with orders to quickly cremate him.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: မင်းမြတ်နိုင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 7, around 60 junta personnel raided and set fire to Yone Lay Kone Village in Budalin Township, Sagaing Region. The junta personnel burnt down around 40 houses. They also arrested Grade 11 student Min Myat Naing and killed him after torturing him.

On April 7, at around 11 a.m., two youth were riding on a motorbike when the junta forces fired at them near Maw Ton Village, Ban La Mot Village Tract in Tanintharyi Township, Tanintharyi Region. One was killed, and the other was captured and detained. The deceased was Kyaw Htwe from Hton Nwe Village, Tanintharyi Township.

On April 5, at around 4 a.m., around 60 junta personnel raided and opened fire at Dan Taing Village in Budalin Township, Sagaing Region. The personnel killed local Min Aye by gunshot and injured two others.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဂျေစောဇာထန်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 10, at 12 p.m., junta forces conducted an airstrike on Webula Town in Falam Township, Chin State, killing nine locals by artillery shrapnel and injuring four others. The nine deceased are J Saw Za Thang, Thawng Za Uk, Thian Sung, Salai Biak Hlai Ceu, Za Hnem Kim, Salai Nathan Hrin Sang, Salai Noah San Lian, Saw Hlai Kim, and Chit Min Thu. The deceased were buried in accordance with Christian customs on April 11 at 9 a.m.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldHfL2UA8oU0Imne: Win Min Htwe (aka) Arr Ti Ti
cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဝင်းမင်းထွေး (ခ) အားတီတီ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 4, Win Min Htwe (aka Arr Ti Ti) was inspected at a junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee joint checkpoint between Chat Thin Village and Koe Taung Boet Village, in Kanbalu Township, Sagaing Region. The personnel found a picture of him wearing a People's Defense Force uniform in his phone and arrested him. On the morning of April 5, the junta's Light Infantry Battalion No. 521 informed Win Min Htwe's family of his death. However, his body was not returned to his family. Win Min Htwe was a local of Nang Khwin Village in Mogaung Township, Kachin State.

On April 12, at around 1 a.m., the junta's No. 28 Police Battalion fired an artillery shell from the side of Pathein-Monywa Street in Yinmarbin Township, Sagaing Region. cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ရိုမှင်းထန်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: Car driver Ro Hming Thang was forcibly recruited to carry weaponry and rations for the junta forces to Hakha Town, Chin State. On April 13, he died after suffering injuries during a clash near Chuncung Village in Hakha Township between the junta forces and Chin National Army, along with their regional allied forces. His car was destroyed by fire.

On April 9, junta forces raided Si Thar Village in Shwegu Township, Kachin State, and arrested 10 locals, including a man named Soe Kyaw, who has a mental illness. Then they killed nine of them and left the village. Afterwards, the bodies of the nine were discovered. The deceased are Mya Aye, Than Cho, Htwe, Aung Myo Khaing, Maung Naing, Sein Win, Myat Nyein, Khin Nwe Oo, and Soe Moe. The whereabouts of Soe Kyaw are still unknown.

On the morning of April 19, a coalition of junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee militia members, totaling around 100 personnel, raided Mya Kan Village in Khin-U Township, Sagaing Region. During the raid, the personnel fired heavy weaponry and clashed with the People's Defence Forces. While the PDF members were retreating, the junta forces captured and killed five PDF members: Tayote Gyi, Moe Hein, Phoe Kyaw, Naung, and Kyaw Naing. Their bodies were discovered with gunshot wounds and their eyes gouged out. Moreover, while leaving the village, the junta forces took five local men as hostages.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldHfL2UA8oU0Imne: Kaung Wai Yan Oo (aka) Ko Thar Gyi
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 21, at around 11 a.m., junta forces tried to pull over a car traveling towards Yebyu Town, Tanintharyi Region. The junta forces shot at the car allegedly because the driver did not stop. The junta's shot resulted in the death of one man: Kaung Wai Yan Oo (aka Ko Thar Gyi) from Thit To Htaung Village, Yebyu Township. His family took his body back to their home village.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: မင်းမင်းသန့်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 21, at around 3 p.m., Infantry Battalion-228 of the junta forces fired heavy weaponry at Hto Mar Village, Kale Township, Sagaing Region. An artillery shell explosion inside the village killed Min Min Thant and Myo Htwe from getting hit by shrapnel while 3 locals were injured.

On April 23, at around 9 a.m., Lat encountered a military column of around 30 junta personnel while he was working in a rubber plantation near Mar Ran Village in Khamaukgyi Town, Tanintharyi Region. The junta forces shot him dead for no apparent reason.

On April 22, at 10 a.m., two people were arrested and shot dead at a junta checkpoint gate in Pala Town, Palaw Township, Tanintharyi Region. The deceased were Kyaw Tun and his son, who were both from Kywel Village in Palaw Township. They were arrested and killed while they were going to meet Kyaw Tun's wife.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ထွန်းထွန်းဝင်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On the afternoon of April 23, junta forces attacked Tabayin Kwel Village in Sagaing Township, Sagaing Region, and got into a clash with the local People's Defense Force. Afterwards, the junta forces arrested and killed local Tun Tun Win. On April 24, the military column left the area, and Tun Tun Win's body was found in the village with his head decapitated and his genitalia cut off and put in his mouth.

On March 24, junta forces raided Man Hae Village in Indaw Township, Sagaing Region and abducted five locals: Nyi Nyi, Law Shote, Aung Min Thike, Nay Linn Tun, and Phoe Shan. On April 24, their bodies, which were chopped up and burned, were discovered in a jungle southeast of Maw Lu Town.

On the morning of April 24, a clash broke out between local defense forces and Pyu Saw Htee militiamen in Pin Taung Village, which is near Zee Taw Village, in Pauk Township, Magway Region. At 2 p.m. that day, the Pyu Saw Htee militiamen raided the village; burned Kyaw Lwin, who had a mental illness, alive; and set around 150 houses on fire.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldHfL2UA8oU0Imne: Aung Kyi Min (aka) Note Khan Hmway
cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အောင်ကြည်မင်း (ခ) နှုတ်ခမ်းမွှေး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 24, the body of Aung Kyi Min (aka Note Khan Hmway) was discovered shot in the head in front of HAPPY KTV in Ma Shei Ka Htaung Ward, Hpakant Township, Kachin State. On February 13, 2023, in Pa Zup Yan Village, Aung Kyi Min ran into the junta forces and was arrested. At the time, he was returning from Lone Khin Village, Hpakant Township.

On April 25, around 100 junta personnel were attacking Shwe Hlay Village, Salingyi Township, Sagaing Region. On that day around 9 a.m., the junta ran into and shot at two locals who were driving a motorbike on Shwe Hlay Village Bridge along Nyaung Pin Gyi - Salingyi Road. Motorbike driver Win Naung was shot, and then he was killed by being stabbed in the stomach with a knife. The motorbike passenger riding with Win Naung managed to escape.

On April 21, junta forces fired heavy weaponry at Kalar Kwel Village in Nawnghkio Township, Shan State. One of the artillery shells exploded on a house in the village, killing two civilians. The deceased were Chit San from Kalar Kwel Village and 82-year-old Santi Mar from Taung Kone San Village, Nawnghkio Township.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: သက်နိုင်ထွန်း (ခ) ဖက်တီး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 25, the bodies of three men were discovered in a field between Ma Kyee Htan Village and Phaung Ka Tar Village in Salingyi Township, Sagaing Region. The bodies had gunshot wounds in their heads and chests. One of the bodies belonged to Thet Naing Tun (aka Fatty) who was a member of Monywa District People's Defense Force. Junta forces arrested him in Monywa Township on March 12.

On April 27, at around 3:30 p.m., junta forces bombed Tan Lan Lo Village in Thantlang Township, Chin State, with a fighter plane. This airstrike killed two people, including a teacher who was part of the Civil Disobedience Movement, and at least five people were injured. Additionally, the airstrike destroyed houses and a monastery in the village.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 21, over 100 junta personnel raided Mhaw Pone Village, Lone Hkin Village Tract, Hpakant Township, Kachin State, and took over 100 locals, including a local named Htwae Sann Aung (aka Thar Gyi), with them into Hsan Hkar (Ma Zup Yan) Detainment Cell. Afterward, they released around 50 locals. On April 30, according to information the family members of Htwae Sann Aung (aka Thar Gyi) that he had died from being beaten in Hsan Hkar (Ma Zup Yan) Detention Cell's interrogation center.

In the morning of May 1, a body of a man was found near Kyauk Sein Taung Bridge in Ma Shee Ka Htaung Ward, Hpakant Town, Kachin State, who was beaten, tortured and shot dead after getting arrested by the junta forces. The deceased was Aung Kyaw Oo from Hmaw Wam Ward, Hpakant Township, and he actively participated in a strike against the military coup.

On April 29, LIB-369 of the junta forces, stationed in No.1 High School at Kawlin Town, Sagaing Region, fired heavy weaponry indiscriminately. One of the artillery shells exploded on a vendor shop on War Yone Tone Street, killing Mi Mone immediately, who was selling salad.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 27, junta forces raided and set fire to Hsin Phyu Seik Village, Tigyaing Township, Sagaing Region; burning down around 40 houses. They also took two locals Kyaw Zin Win and Taing Chit as hostages and shot them dead.

On April 23, regional defense forces attacked a vehicle column of the junta forces with a handmade explosive near Aung Chan Thar Village, Madaya Township, Mandalay Region. That evening, the junta forces killed Phoe Htaung from Mahar Local People's Defense Force, whom they had captured and beheaded.
On April 24, junta forces attacked U Mhin Village, Tada-U Township, Mandalay Region, and shot dead a local named Aung Htwe after capturing him.

On April 30 and May 1, over 100 junta personnel attacked Sagaing Township, Sagaing Region, and within two days captured 2 members of the Sagaing Township People's Defense Forces. On May 1, the junta forces killed Bu Thee, Branch Commander of No.8 Battalion of Sagaing District PDF, by cutting down from the neck to the pubic region and then beheading him. On April 30, the junta forces also killed Ah Shay Gyi, a member of Sagaing Township People's Defense Team.

On April 30, the junta forces also killed Ah Shay Gyi, a member of Sagaing Township People's Defense Team.

On the evening of May 2, junta forces carried out bombings with 2 fighter jets in Hle Lan Ku, Tha Yet Tan, Kywel Lan and Bon Ma Tee Villages in Htantabin Township, Bago Region. A bomb landed on Kywel Lan Village and as a result a local named Su Hlaing Aye was hit by shrapnel; severing her head and arm and killing her immediately. Ye Soe Aung and Lae Lae Khaing, who were a married couple, were also hit by shrapnel. They were transported to the hospital but later died. Due to the airstrike, a rural hospital in Hle Lan Ku Village was also destroyed.

In the morning of May 2, junta forces raided villages in Pakokku Township, Magway Region, in great numbers. Sel Lan Villager Wai Lu Kyaw encountered a military column of the junta forces in his chilli fields and was shot dead by them.

On April 26 and 27, junta forces raided and set fire to Myothit Village, Khin-U Township, Sagaing Region. As a result, a local named Tun Win, died in the fire and around 400 houses were burned down. Additionally, a woman was captured and beaten; suffering serious injuries as a result.

On April 30, at approximately 8 a.m., around 80 junta personnel raided and opened fire in Ywar Ma Village, Sagaing  Township, Sagaing Region. They captured around 100 civilians including local People's Defense Team member Htu Shay, and after interrogating them at the village monastery, they were released. On May 1, when the military left the village, the body of Htu Shay was found with his hands tied, near the village cemetery. He had been shot dead, and his body had injuries consistent with torture.

On April 28, around 100 junta personnel from Light Infantry Division 88 raided and set fire to Myay Mon Village, Kanbalu Township, Sagaing Region. Nay Hline Tun was captured after running into the junta forces near the village. On April 29, his body was discovered with wounds inflicted by a blade.

cellValuesByColumnId.fld7KLBHB6DdATjnu: U Maung Pu + Daw Thein Myint
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On February 24, 2022, junta forces arrested Ye Mon Thein (aka Pu Lone) from No.3 Ward, Yae Ni Town, Yedashe Township, Bago Region, on suspicion of being involved in the explosion of Sittaung River Bridge. He died during the interrogation.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldHfL2UA8oU0Imne: Saw Lay Lay Htoo (aka) Phoe Khwar Lay (aka) Wunna
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On May 3, at around 7 p.m., Saw Lay Lu Htoo (aka Phoe Khwar, aka Wunna) ran into junta forces near Nat Than Kwin Rural Hospital while he was returning home on a motorbike. He was shot at by the junta forces. He suffered a bullet wound in the waist as a result and died while being treated at Nat Than Kwin Rural Hospital. He was working at a car workshop in Nat Than Kwin Village Tract, Kyaukkyi Township, Bago Region.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: လာလ်ပန့်ဆန်းငါ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On January 24, 2023, the junta arrested Lal Pang Sann Ngar for encouraging people to join the Civil Disobedience Movement and participating in protests himself after the coup. On February 24, he was sentenced to serve two years in prison under Penal Code Section 505(a). Then, the junta informed his family members that he died suddenly while being detained at Mawlaikkalay Prison on March 21. His family retrieved his body and buried him in Myar Zaw Village in Falam Township, Chin State, where he had resided before his death.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: မြင့်ထွန်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 4, junta forces arrested NLD Township executive member Myint Tun in his home at Inn Gyi Village, Mhan Kyee Kone Village Tract, Paungde Township, Bago Region, and took him to Hmat Taing Police Station. More than a week after his arrest, his family was informed of his death and that his body was at Pyay Town 100 Beds Hospital. When his body was cremated on May 4, the junta told the family that only 2 family members were allowed to be present, however none of his family members attended to the funeral.

On May 4, at 2 p.m., junta forces used 3 jet fighter planes to bomb Pait Khayar Village, Mingin Township, Sagaing Region. A bomb shell exploded on a school, killing 7 locals including 3 children and injuring another 7 locals. The deceased were Myint Win, Than Swe, Ohn Sein, Mar Mar Aye, Zarni Linn Khet, May Su Naing and Ei Ei Soe.

On May 5, at around 8 a.m., a clash broke out between junta forces and local defense forces near Let Htote Taw Village, Myinmu Township, Sagaing Region. Then on May 6, junta forces raided and set fire to the village. A local named Aung Soe was trapped in the village, he was beaten and tortured, and later died from the fire as he could not flee. Over 500 houses were burned down subsequently.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On the evening of April 26, the Battalion Commander of Kawlin District Battalion-1, Du Jum Hkalen Zau Seng and Ko Ye, a member of the People's Defense Force were arrested during a confrontation with the junta forces at Thae Kaw Village, Kawlin Township, Sagaing Region. They were then shot dead and their bodies were set on fire.

They were then shot dead and their bodies were set on fire.

On the morning of May 4, Bo Bo from Aye Chan Tharyar Yay Street, Oak Pho Ward, Phyu Township, Bago Region, was inspected by a policeman while he was out shopping, and it was discovered that he did not have a motorbike license. Because of this, he was taken to Phyu Township Police Station. Afterwards, he was detained and charged with Export and Import Law. 3 days later, on May 7, at 2 a.m., his family was informed of his death caused by torture. When his family went to the police station, they were informed that his body was sent to Phyu Township People's Hospital. At the time of his arrest, he was a healthy person and his death record said he died from natural causes.

Among the deceased were two members of Chaung-U Township People's Defense Force and two members of local People's Defense Team, who were all killed by decapitation, along with killing a local. In addition, the junta forces killed 2 members of Aung San Force PDF, who were helping to extract the internally displaced people, and an internally displaced woman.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On May 8, a coalition of junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee militiamen, around 30 personnel in total, captured Tun Tun Linn, a local of Lel Taw Village, Monywa Township, Sagaing Region, for no apparent reason. They were interrogating him after taking him to a primary school in Pa Yit Kone Village. He was tortured and killed during the interrogation. His body was discovered in front of the school.
