cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On May 8, at around 5 p.m., a coalition of around 7 junta personnel and U Shwe Min militiamen arrived at a toll gate in Sadung Town, Waingmaw Township, Kachin State, and opened fire. As a result, 2 locals: Maran Ja Li Htum Ja and Arr Ti, and a vendor at the toll gate, were shot and died immediately from their injuries.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On May 6, at around 7 p.m., Linn Htet Aung, was driving a motorbike and was hit by a car driven by Border Guard Force (BGF) near Thingan Nyi Nyaung Village Monastery, Myawaddy Township, Kayin State. The car did not stop and continued driving, which resulted in the death of Linn Htet Aung. The locals tried to help him but the BGF opened fire to scare them away.

As a result, the junta forces captured 19 locals, including 4 children and 11 women. They then tied them up and burned them alive in two groups. In addition, another local was brutally tortured and killed in Nyaung Pin Thar Village cemetery.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On May 11, at around 7 a.m., while junta forces were raiding Na Bu Taw Village, Yinmarbin Township, Sagaing Region, they opened fire at the fleeing locals. As a result, Naing Oo (aka Al Bo) was shot dead, whilst at least 10 locals were injured.

On the morning of May 12, around 100 junta personnel opened fire at a house hosting a remembrance prayer, where alms food was being offered to monks (traditionally, alms are offered to monks on the seventh day of a person’s demise), in Htan Zin Village, Bant Bway Village Tract, Yinmarbin Township, Sagaing Region. As a result, 2 women were killed immediately while a mother and her 4-month-old baby were injured. Afterwards, while they were being treated, the mother, Phyu Phyu Thin, died.

As a result, 2 women were killed immediately while a mother and her 4-month-old baby were injured. Afterwards, while they were being treated, the mother, Phyu Phyu Thin, died.

On May 12, from 7 a.m. to 2 p.m., around 50 junta personnel fired heavy weaponry indiscriminately while they were attacking Mohnyin Township, Kachin State. As a result, an artillery shell exploded on a house in Nam Mar Town and Sein Win died from getting struck by the artillery shell shrapnel.

On May 11, at around 6:30 p.m., junta forces raided and set fire to Ngar Yan Village, Chaung-U Township, Sagaing Region. Additionally they fired heavy weaponry indiscriminately; killing a local named San Linn on the spot, whilst seriously injuring his wife. Moreover, the military column set fire to the houses in the village, burning down around 200 houses.

On May 10, at around 7 a.m., junta forces who were on a hidden watch near Nga Wun River Bridge, opened fire at 8 locals traveling on 4 motorbikes near Kayin Taw Village, Lemyethna Township, Ayeyarwady Region, out of suspicion. As a result, Kyaw Swar and Shine Ko Ko were killed from gunshot wounds and 4 locals, including a woman, were arrested while 2 others managed to escape. After inspecting the bodies at the mortuary of Lemyethna People's Hospital, the junta forces took the bodies and cremated them, instead of returning the bodies to their families.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ခင်ရွှေဝင်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On May 17, at around 4:20 a.m., junta forces carried out aerial bombings with a fighter jet at Saw Lone Village, Bawlake Township, Kayah State. As a result, 17-year-old Khin Shwe Win was killed, while her father and 3 other locals were injured. Due to the aerial bombing, 6 houses, 2 pharmacies and a monastery in the village were destroyed.

On January 9, 2023, junta forces on a hidden watch near Kyar Kan Monastery, Aungmingalar Ward, Khin-U Town, Sagaing Region, shot at Kyaw Myo Khaing and arrested him. Then on the morning of January 11, while questioning him in Myoma Police Station, junta forces shot and killed him.

On January 14, 2023, junta forces took Khaing Soe Thant from Kyauk Phyu Taing Village, Salingyi Township, Sagaing Region, to use him as a human shield. On the morning of January 19, his body, which was badly beaten, was discovered in a Palm tree forest near Shwe Hlay (North) Village.

On March 12, 2023, junta forces arrested 7 People's Defense Force (PDF) members, who were in Nan Da Wun Ward, Monywa Township, Sagaing Region. Afterwards, 4 of them were found dead near Aout Seik Taw Village with gunshot wounds. Their names were Wai Linn Oo, Nge Oo, Thura Zaw and Aung Myo Nyein.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: စိုးမင်းဦး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On March 27, 2023, Soe Min Oo from Kan Gyi Village, Zigon Township, Bago Region, was going to Okpho Town, to buy groceries for his wedding, when he mistakenly entered a police watchpost in Wine Village, Okpho Township. The personnel from the police watchpost arrested him. Afterwards, on March 28, at around 1 p.m., he was taken to the village cemetery and killed. They also took 2,000,000 Kyats that he had with him.

On the evening of April 3, 2023, junta personnel came to the house of NLD party supporter Win Kyaw in Sa Lein Ward, Pyigyitagon Township, Mandalay Region, with two private cars. Win Kyaw was asked about his NLD party member wife, who was evading arrest, and they shot at him; injuring him in the thigh and shoulder. He was taken to Mandalay Royal Palace Interrogation Center afterwards. Then, on the afternoon of April 4, the junta forces told the family to retrieve the body of Win Kyaw at the mortuary in Mandalay People's Hospital. When his body was recovered, injuries on his face, head and back, consistent with beating and torture, were found.

​​On April 3, 2023, junta forces stationed themselves in Pyin Taw Oo Village, Kale Town, Sagaing Region. When they left the village on April 6, the body of Salai Sui Khaw Muang, who was killed by torture, was found on the road going from Pyin Taw Oo Village to Nan Saung Pu Village. The man in question was visiting Pyin Khon Gyi Village, Kale Township, Sagaing Region, from Bwar Khwer Village, Falam Township, Chin State. On April 3, he went missing when he left for Thar Yar Kone Village from Pyin Khon Gyi Village.
On February 15, 2023, at around 11 a.m., junta forces attacked Taung Ywar Ma Village, Seikphyu Township, Magway Region, and opened fire; killing Yin Yin, who was physically impaired, immediately.

On February 9, 2023, at around 2 a.m., Naing Vin from Mawt Ka Nin Village, Ye Township, Mon State, ran into the junta forces while he was on his way to work at a rubber plantation. The junta personnel shot at him, killing him immediately.

On March 23, 2023, at around 7 p.m., junta forces in front of No.61 Infantry Battalion checkpoint shot at Kyi Win and Lay Nge, who were driving on a motorbike from Ye Town to Phar Gyi Village. The checkpoint was located near Kyon Laung Village, Ye Township, Mon State. Kyi Win was shot and despite being taken to Ye Town Hospital, he died at 9 p.m. that day. The whereabouts of Lay Nge who was riding the motorbike along with Kyi Win are unknown.

On January 7, 2023, at 10:30 a.m., junta forces carried out aerial bombing with fighter planes on Yar Yi Hta Village, Lel Htoo Hpoe Area, Mae Thu Village Tract, Hpapun Township, Kayin State. The bomb shells exploded in a local workplace; killing Nwe Ni, her two sons, her daughter-in-law, and two other workers.

On January 9, 2023, junta forces shot and killed Pa Lal Lian Thawng while he was driving a motorbike in Kale Town, Sagaing Region. His body was sent to Kale Town People's Hospital on January 10 and his family took his body back to Htan Hni Yar Village, Falam Township, Chin State, on January 11.

On January 9, 2023, at around 10 p.m., junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee members arrested and tortured a local named Min Naing, who was driving a motorbike near the administration office of Shat Pon Village, Palaw Township, Tanintharyi Region. Min Naing was sent to Palaw Hospital but due to the severity of his injuries, he was sent to Myeik Hospital overnight. Then on January 11, he was sent from Myeik Hospital to Yangon Hospital but he died on the way from the wounds he suffered during torture.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အောင်မြင့်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On January 18, 2023, around 100 junta personnel came into Kyauk Kar Village, Monywa Township, Sagaing Region, and captured Aung Myint, who was from Nyaung Pin Village. They shot him dead after beating him with a bamboo stick. Then, his body was set on fire along with 11 houses in Kyauk Kar (South) Village. The junta forces set fire to his pea field and took valuable properties from inside his house.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldHfL2UA8oU0Imne: Chit Yin Htoo (aka) Sar Pu Tee
cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ချစ်ရင်ထူး (ခ) စာပုတီး
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On March 5, 2023, at around 2 p.m., 12-year-old Chit Yin Htoo (aka Sar Pu Tee) found an unexploded 79 mm artillery shell fired by the junta forces, while he was returning home after herding cows. He brought the shell to his home in A Lel Sho Village, Khin-U Township, Sagaing Region. While the shell was placed on a water well in the yard, it fell down and exploded, killing him.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဝေမင်းနောင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On the night of March 11, 2023, junta forces shot at a family, who were working on a fish farm in Mi Kyaung Kan Village, Shwebo Township, Sagaing Region. As a result, Wai Min Naung was shot in the head and killed, while his parents managed to get away. On March 12, his body was found disposed of inside the fish farm.

On March 21, 2023, at 12 p.m., junta forces fired at the civilians living near farms outside of Pa Lai (aka) Pan Hlaing Village, Shwebo Township, Sagaing Region, with a sniper rifle. As a result, a villager named San Nu was shot in the neck and died.

On the morning of March 23, 2023, junta forces came to Kyauk Sel Lay Village, Madaya Township, Mandalay Region, and shot at 4 People's Defense Force (PDF) members but they managed to get away. Afterwards, the junta forces captured 3 locals and the decapitated body of Win Htwe was discovered in a mango field at the entrance of the village.

On July 24, 2022, at around 10 a.m., over 20 Pyu Saw Htee militiamen from Inn Ma Htee Village came into Loke Thar Village, Pale Township, Sagaing Region, and opened fire. As a result, the locals had to flee for safety. However, Hlaw Kar Villager Min Ko, who did not escape in time, was beaten and tortured by the Pyu Saw Htee, before being shot dead.

On July 25, 2022, Pyu Saw Htee militiamen, subservient to the junta, shot and killed Ae Tun somewhere in a field 7 furlongs north of Hle Seik Village. He was from Hle Seik Village, Myothit Township (Sub), Tamu Township, Sagaing Region.

On the evening of March 28, 2023, Kyaw Linn was working in a field between Kyu Thar and Kan Thar Villages, Tilin Township, Magway Region, when he hit an unexploded 40 mm bombshell; setting it off. He was killed from the explosion while a local working with him in the field was injured.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဇာခြည်ဝင်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On March 30, 2023, at around 8 a.m., junta forces fired heavy weaponry into Nyaung Pin Thar Village, Tigyaing Township, Sagaing Region. As a result, a local named Zar Chi Win was killed from artillery shrapnel.
On the morning of April 2, 2023, junta forces raided Sit Tan Village, Tigyaing Township, Sagaing Region. The junta forces shot and killed a local named Than Pe Lay while he was trying to get away.

On April 5 and 6 of 2023, a clash broke out between Karen National Liberation Army (KNLA) coalition forces and a military assistance column under Division 22 of the junta forces, in Kawkareik Town, Kayin State. Afterwards, No.97 Infantry Battalion of the junta forces fired various weaponry at areas where there were no clashes taking place. As a result, a local named Win Than was killed and houses were destroyed.

On the evening of April 8, 2023, patrolling junta forces shot at 2 men from Ran Pho Village, Ban La Mot Village Tract, Tanintharyi Township, Tanintharyi Region. As a result, Cho Pote was killed while another man was able to get away.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ခင်မောင်ဝင်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 8, 2023, Khin Maung Win from Koe Pin Village, Pale Township, Sagaing Region, was going to buy Palm Tree Juice in Me Za Yat Village, when he encountered a military column of the junta forces and was captured. Afterwards, his burnt body was found between Ta Laing Kan and Thayet Kan Villages.

On April 8, 2023, during a clash between junta forces and people's defence forces at Pa Wut Kone Village, Palaw Township, Tanintharyi Region, the junta forces opened fire; injuring 4 locals. One of them was 30-year-old Kyaw Soe from the village, who was seriously injured while driving a motorbike and died while being treated at Palaw Hospital.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: စောသီဟဇော်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: ​​On the afternoon of April 4, 2023, junta forces shot and killed a local named Saw Thiha Zaw on the road to the cemetery near Let Pan Phyu Village, Kyauk Ta Ga Village Tract, Leik Tho Town, Thandaunggyi Township, Kayin State.
On March 27, 2021, junta forces carried out aerial bombing in Day Pu Noet Village, Hpapun Township, Kayin State; killing 3 locals: Saw Gee Doh; Saw Tar Balu Soe; Saw Lo Boe, and injuring 8 locals.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: စောတာဘလုစိုး

On April 9, 2023, around 40 personnel from Northwestern Command Headquarters, based in Monywa Town, of the junta forces, raided and set fire on Nyaung Oak Village, Myaing Township, Magway Region. They then shot and killed mentally unwell Aung Zaw Linn from Thae Gyi Village, who was in Nyaung Oak Village at the time.

On April 12, 2023, at 4:30 p.m., an artillery division of the junta forces, based in Kyaukhtu Town, fired heavy weaponry at Tay Village near Kyaukhtu Town, Saw Township, Magway Region, without any clash taking place. As a result, car workshop worker Kyaw Lwin Oo from Na Thoe Village was killed and two other people were injured.

On May 10, junta forces arrested Mya Min Htet and Thet Thet Oo, a couple living in Tan Ngar Kone Village, Waing Village Tract, Okpho Township, Bago Region, near Thar Si Village, Gyobingauk Township, for allegedly being involved with the People's Defense Force. They were taken to the Pyay Operation Command Headquarters. From there, they were taken to No.6 Light Infantry Battalion base. On May 19, the junta forces made the couple show them the location of  PDF bases in Bago Yoma mountains. They shot and killed the couple between Kaing Cho Gyi Village and Let Pann Pin Khone Village, Okpho Township.

On the evening of May 15, junta forces arrested Kyaw Thura from Daung Ngu Ward, Dawei Town, Tanintharyi Region, and took him to the interrogation center. Afterwards, on May 20, Daung Ngu Ward administrator reported to his family members about the death of Kyaw Thura. However, the family members do not yet know the date of his death.

On the morning of May 18, junta forces fired heavy weaponry at villages in Kyaukkyi Township, Bago Region. An artillery shell explosion in Kyun Taw Village resulted in the death of 14-year old Min Ye Hset, who was hit with shrapnel, and the injury of two other locals who were also hit with shrapnel. Additionally, due to the shelling, a monastery and a house were destroyed.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldHfL2UA8oU0Imne: Zaw Tun Naing (aka) Day War Nar
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On June 26, 2022, junta forces arrested Zaw Tun Naing (aka Day War Nar) from Myo Hla Town, Yedashe Township, Bago Region, for allegedly supporting the People's Defense Force (PDF). Then, while being detained at Taungoo Prison, he became unwell. On May 22, 2023, he died from hypertension and heart problems while being treated at Taungoo Hospital.

On the evening of May 18, a clash took place between around 70 junta personnel from No.415 Light Infantry Battalion and the People's Defense Force, between Min Lel and Ka Dat Chaung Villages in Katha Township, Sagaing Region. Then, on the morning of May 19, junta forces came into Min Lel Village and shot at the locals. As a result, Nyo Nyo and Aye Aye Aung were shot in the chest and killed immediately, while 3 other locals were seriously injured.

On May 17, at 7 a.m., junta forces fired heavy weaponry at Htain Taw Village, Kanbalu Township, Sagaing Region. An artillery shell exploded in a betel nut field in the village, striking a couple with shrapnel who were picking betel leaves. The wife Mya Nu Thein was killed immediately. Moreover, the aforementioned military column shot and killed Hsann Soe Aung, who had been seeking refuge in a jungle near Ywar Thit Village, Kanbalu Township, when he ran into the military column.

cellValuesByColumnId.fld7KLBHB6DdATjnu: U Sein Win + Daw Aye Nwet
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On October 18, 2021, junta forces arrested Myo Kyaw Thu (aka Aung Moe Zaw), along with his wife, on Thanlwin Bridge, Kayin State, for allegedly supporting the PDF. While being detained in Hpa-An Prison, he suffered an aneurysm due to hypertension and died as he did not get medical treatment and died on October 19, 2022.

On May 6, junta forces arrested and detained retired school teacher Thaung Yii from Yone Pin Village, Taungtha Township, Mandalay Region, at Taungtha Myoma Police Station. On May 23, his family were informed by the police station that he had died on May 18. The junta forces had already cremated his body.

On May 24, junta forces fired various weapons and eventually raided Taung Mwar Village in Ayadaw Township, Sagaing Region. As a result, 80-year-old Yar Nyunt and Hla Htay were killed by artillery shrapnel, and 80-year-old Khin Sein and 60-year-old Aye Htoke were killed by fire. Additionally, a man named Min Min was shot to death. Bodies of the 5 victims were discovered after the military column left the village.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On the morning of May 24, junta forces raided and set fire to Ma Kyee Su Village, Myingyan Township, Mandalay Region. Khin Maung Htay, who had previously suffered from a stroke, and 60-year-old Aye Kyaing, were killed in the fire as they were unable to run away and remained in the village.

On the morning of May 24, junta forces raided and set fire to Ma Kyee Su Village, Myingyan Township, Mandalay Region. Khin Maung Htay, who had previously suffered from a stroke, and 60-year-old Aye Kyaing, were killed in the fire as they were unable to run away and remained in the village.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: မင်းလှိုင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On May 23, junta forces raided villages in Kawlin Township, Sagaing Region. They then captured and killed People's Defense Team fighter Nay Hsann Aung from Kyay Inn Village, homoeopathic doctor Thein Aye from Kyauk Kar Village, Kyaw Min Thein and Min Hlaing from Maung Kaw Village. In addition, the junta forces shot and killed Phoe Wa, a refugee from Kanbalu Township, while he was herding cows at the entrance of Aout Thi Ta Yar Village. The five bodies were discovered on May 24.

cellValuesByColumnId.fld7KLBHB6DdATjnu: U Naing Oo Lwin + Daw Nilar Myint
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 29 2023, junta forces arrested Nay Linn Oo from Thanlyin Township, Yangon Region, and brought him to Thanlyin Myoma Police Station. On May 23, the police station informed his family members that he died on May 2 at the interrogation center. His family was unable to retrieve his body.

On September 9, at approximately 11 a.m., around 30 junta personnel raided Myin Thar Village, Gangaw Township, Magway Region, and opened fire using heavy weaponry. They set fire to over 30 houses, arrested locals and killed 18 villagers. The villagers who were killed are as follows; Tun Ngwe, Aung Tin, Aung Ngwe, Yan Aye, Kyaw Hsann, Doe Maung Maung, and those under 18 years of age; Pyae Phyo Win, Nyein Sithu, Phyo Zaw Min, Thet Tun Aung, Shine Htet Aung, Ah Ngal Lay, Htet Naing Oo, Pyone Maung Maung, Shein Phone Naing, Naing Myo Tun, Ah Pu Lay and Aung Naing.

On the evening of May 21, junta forces arrested Thet Naung from Taung Khin Yan Village, Gangaw Township, Magway Region, for allegedly being part of PDF. On May 22, his family members discovered his decapitated body in the Myit Thar River.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On April 1 2023, at around 8:20 pm, junta forces fired 2 rounds of 120 mm artillery shells at Bway Htaw Yoe Village, Kwam Pin Wa Village Tract, Hpapun Township, Kayin State. The shells exploded in the village; with shrapnel killing a 72-year-old woman. Four other family members were injured including a 2-month old and a 5-year old child.

On May 22, junta forces tortured 16-year-old Wai Phoe Oo from Kawthoung Township, Tanintharyi Region. Then, he was shot and killed. The junta forces had arrested him for allegedly supporting the People's Defense Force (PDF).

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On May 25, at around 2:30 p.m., junta forces fired 60mm artillery shells at the civilian villages, from a street branch in front of a bridge in Kyaikdon Town, Kawkareik Township, Kayin State. As a result, 13-year-old Than Naing Oo was killed from a shrapnel going through his back, and his throat. An 8-year-old child was also injured, and the child was rushed to the hospital for treatment.

On May 26, at around 8 a.m., over 200 junta personnel raided River Island area in Yesagyo Township, Magway Region, in three military columns and opened fire with heavy weaponry. An artillery shell exploded in Mi Pha Yar Village; killing a local named Khin Aye Po, while injuring a 12-year-old child.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On May 2, Cin Hau Vung (aka Linn Linn) and Lian Za Thawn were traveling to Hakha Town, Chin State. They were captured en route and killed by the junta forces, without the knowledge of their family members. Lian Za Thawn was serving in Laboratory-2 of Hakha People's Hospital and had joined the Civil Disobedience Movement. Their burnt bodies were found on Thi Phol Street, Hni Yar Lay Lawn New Village, once the junta forces stationed there had left.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldHfL2UA8oU0Imne: Pyae Phyo Win (aka) Mae Mae Gyi
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: After the military coup in 2021, Pyae Phyo Win (aka Mae Mae Gyi) participated in the protests and got arrested by junta forces in May 2021. On June 11, 2021, Dagon Myothit (South) Township Military Tribunal sentenced him to serve 7 years in prison under Section 505 and 436 of the Penal Code. After being imprisoned at Insein Prison, he was transferred to Thayarwady Prison in January 2023, along with other political prisoners. On the night of May 21, 2023, Thayarwady Prison informed his family members of his death, and informed them that they could view his body. Hence, his family members went to see him on March 22.

On May 26, at around 11:30 a.m., junta forces abducted Win Htay along with a young man in Htantabin Township, Bago Region, in order to use them as human shields. This occurred while they were in the process of attacking the township. The junta forces eventually released the young man at approximately 6 pm. On May 29, at around 4:30 p.m., the body of Win Htay was discovered with a bullet wound in his temple on the outskirts of the jungles near Tha Pyay Nyunt Village.

On the afternoon of May 28, junta forces fired artillery shells at Kha Name Moo Extension Ward, No. 7 Ward, Kawkareik Town, Kayin State; killing a couple people (named below) who were riding their motorbike at the time. They were killed by an artillery shrapnel hitting Phoe Kyar on the head and thigh, and Khin Myat Htwe on their neck, hands and legs.

Moreover, the military column raided and set fire to Yay Shar Village, located near Nann Oo Village. They also shot and killed Zaw Win who was trying to put out fires.

Additionally, they arrested people who were considered to be suspicious. Subsequently, the junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee militiamen shot and killed Zaw Linn Maung from Pyit Htae (South) Village and Kyaw Wai from Kaing Lel Village.

An artillery shell exploded in a village; killing a local identified as Kyu Hline. She was struck by shrapnel on her chest. Additionally, Soe Gyi, who lived near Taung Market, was killed by shrapnel striking his head.

Phoe Thar Gyi died from the shrapnel immediately, while Nga Moe was seriously injured and died while being transported to hospital. Moreover, a local man was also injured.

During the process, they captured a local named Hla Soe Aung and killed him by decapitating him. Then they set his body on fire. Moreover, a 65-year-old man was shot but managed to escape.

On June 2 at around 3 pm, junta forces shot at 2 villagers from Kan To Village, who were driving a motorboat in a river in Nyaung Pin Kone Village, Tanintharyi Township, Tanintharyi Region, for no apparent reason. As a result, Aung Kyaw was shot and fell into the water, while another man was able to swim and get away. Afterwards, on the morning of June 3, the body of Aung Kyaw was discovered in a river in Sin Din Village.

When he got to a junta checkpoint in Kaleinaung Bridge, the junta forces shot at him for allegedly driving away without stopping at the checkpoint. He was shot in the leg but he managed to drive away. Then, he ran into the junta forces again near Su Taung Pyae Pagoda in Kaleinaung Town and was shot dead on the spot.

On May 31, junta forces attacked Taung Twin Village in Mawlaik Township, Sagaing Region. They captured 4 people, including lay attendant Ba Chit, carpenter Maung Aye and Phoe Chit, for allegedly being part of the People's Defense Force. The body of Ba Chit was discovered in a field with gunshot wounds to his stomach, chest and head in Thit Khaung Tee Village. Among the arrested, 15-year-old Phoe Chit was tortured and was released with slash wounds on his body.

He was sent to Loikaw People’s Hospital where he later died.

Four people were killed due to exploding artillery shrapnel, namely a monk Hsann Win from No.3 Ward, Kayin, Pann Aye and 13-year-old Arli from No.6 Ward in Kyainseikgyi Town. Three other locals were seriously injured and brought to hospital for treatment. Moreover, a monastery and a mosque were destroyed in the attack, as well as a charitable funeral service vehicle.

On June 8, at around 9 am, junta forces fired artillery shells at No.5 Ward in Nit Ka Yin Village, Ye Township, Mon State. An artillery shell exploded on a house in the village; injuring a migrant worker named Tin Gyi. She died while being transported to the hospital

On June 7, at approximately 5 am, around 80 junta forces attacked Yay Kan Su Village in Monywa Township, Sagaing Region. They opened fire on a PDF base located in the village. During the attack, they arrested 4 PDF personnel. The junta then shot and killed the 4 PDF members, and proceeded to set their bodies on fire. In addition, the junta forces raided the village. They shot and killed 2 local men who tried to flee out of fear.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On May 31, at around 2 p.m., junta forces arrested People's Administration Team member Myat Thu Linn (aka Ko Van Ji), near Nyaung Pin Market in Salingyi Township, Sagaing Region. On the morning of June 11, his body was found in Htan Taw Seik lumber yard near Nyaung Pin Gyi Village, with injuries indicating that he was tortured.

On June 8, at around 12 p.m., the junta forces were inspecting the phones of locals travelling in Maing Naung Village, in Mohnyin Township, Kachin State. Thein Linn was shot and killed due to his non-compliance with the checks, and allegedly attempting to evade.

On June 9, at around 3 p.m., junta forces fired artillery shells at Pay Too Village, Kyaukkyi Township, Bago Region. An artillery shell exploded in the village, killing Naw Baw Htoo. Subsequently, at approximately 6 p.m. and lasting up to 9 p.m., junta forces fired artillery shells into Yay Twin Kone Village in the same township; killing Saw Hsi Phoe and destroying a house.

On June 9, at around 3 p.m., junta forces fired artillery shells at Pay Too Village, Kyaukkyi Township, Bago Region. An artillery shell exploded in the village, killing Naw Baw Htoo. Subsequently, at approximately 6 p.m. and lasting up to 9 p.m., junta forces fired artillery shells into Yay Twin Kone Village in the same township; killing Saw Hsi Phoe and destroying a house.

On the afternoon of June 11, Wai Yan Hein, an internally displaced person returned to his home in Ya Ngal Village, Thayetchaung Township, Tanintharyi Region in order to retrieve his mother's medicines. His family, along with his mother, were also displaced. He encountered the junta forces present within the village;  he was shot and killed.

On June 9, at around 3 p.m., junta forces fired artillery shells at Yay Le Oo Village in Kale Township, Sagaing Region. As a result, the locals fled into nearby jungles to seek refuge. During the evacuation process, an artillery shrapnel struck Mee Hla in the stomach; killing her instantly. Meanwhile, another unidentified man was injured.

On June 8, at around 5 p.m., junta forces arrive at Mhaw Kaung Village, Hpakant Township, Kachin State, and attempted to arrest Maung Aye, Thein and Myint Lwin. Thein was in his home at the time. The junta forces shot and killed Maung Aye for allegedly resisting arrest and attempting to abscond. They eventually apprehended Thein and Myint Lwin. The 3 of them were in charge of leading urban strikes in Hpakant after the military coup.

On June 8, at around 4 p.m., junta forces fired heavily upon Lwel Wain Village, Saw Lon Village Tract in Bawlake Township, Kayah State. Artillery shells exploded in the village, and as a result, a local identified Aik Nu was found dismembered.

On June 10, at 7 a.m., a coalition of junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee militiamen raided Pi Tauk Pin Village, Kanbalu Township, Sagaing Region. They proceeded to shoot and kill a local identified as Thein Win. Subsequently, at around 8:30 a.m., the military column apprehended a local from Pint Thar Village and used him as a guide.

On June 11, at around 9 p.m., junta forces fired artillery shells at Nyaung Kyan Village, Hpa-An Township, Kayin State. One of them exploded onto a house in the village, and Zaw Min Tun, a resident of the house was killed by shrapnel striking him in the hip and ribs. Zaw Min Tun was from Kha Yit Village, Taikkyi Township in Yangon Region and was in the process of acquiring his son school's leaving certificate.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: After a police station located in Nyaung Pin Gyi Village, Salingyi Township, Sagaing Region was attacked, the junta forces retaliated on June 14, at approximately 9 a.m by firing 40mm and 60mm artillery shells. This resulted in the instant death of an individual in Hnin Taw Village due to sustaining a shrapnel strike to his head, while two other individuals were injured.

On May 4, No. 361 Light Infantry Battalion of the junta forces raided Thayet Kan Village in Kanbalu Township, Sagaing Region. They proceeded to shoot and kill Khaing Zaw in his house. He was reported to be mentally ill.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On May 17, at around 7:30 a.m., a coalition of junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee militiamen encountered two internally displaced men in Kanbalu Township, Sagaing Region. They shot the men; killing one. He was reported as a resident of Ywar Thit Kone Village. He was shot in the head and killed on the spot, while the other man was injured and received emergency assistance and operation.

On June 13, junta forces attacked Thar Zin Village in Sagaing Township, Sagaing Region, and set the village on fire. As a result, 60-year-old Than Mya was killed as she was unable to flee from the fires. Around 700 houses were burned down in the fire.

On June 13, a military column of the junta forces attacked a People's Defence Force (PDF) base in Yesagyo Township, Magway Region, leading to clashes between the two. The junta forces apprehended PDF official Jin Bee. On June 16, his body was found in the Chindwin River with a gunshot wound to his head.

On June 6, junta forces arrested Tin Than Oo while he was at his home, located on 11th Street, Nauk Lel Ward in Myeik Town, Tanintharyi Region. On June 16, the police station informed his family members of his death at around 3 p.m., resulting from from dyspnoea due to a preexisting heart condition. He died while being interrogated at the center. His family members were only allowed to see his face, and the junta cremated his body. The deceased was the brother of Myeik Town NLD Amyotha Hluttaw Representatitive Min Zaw Tint.

In April 2023, junta forces arrested Aung Moe and Tun Naing from Khin Thar Ward, Gangaw Town in Magway Region and detained them at Gangaw Police Station Detainment Center. On June 10, they were taken outside of detainment and on June 11, their bodies were discovered near Pyar Village.

On June 15, at around 6 a.m., approximately 50 junta personnel raided a funeral house owned by a local in Na Nwin Kone Village in Myaung Township, Sagaing Region, and opened fire. As a result, a local identified as Thein Kyaw was killed on the spot.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဆန်းဝင်းအောင်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On the morning of June 17, approximately 80 junta personnel raided Kyee Kone Village in Sagaing Township, Sagaing Region and set it on fire. During the arson attack, they killed a local identified as Hsann Win Aung and set his body on fire. He was discovered after the junta forces departed from the village. 8 houses were burned and destroyed due to the arson operation.

At around 9 p.m. on the same day, an artillery shell exploded on a house located in No.1 Ward, Thein Za Yat Town, killing Aye Aye Nwe and injuring 4 locals, including a 5 year old child.

On June 17, at approximately 8:15 a.m., junta forces fired artillery shells at Chaung Hnit Khwa Village in Thandaunggyi Township, Kayin State. The artillery shells exploded on several houses; killing 60-year-old Naw Ywar Eh Phaw, who sustained shrapnel injuries to her head. The strikes also critically injured a man.

Among the captives were Kyaw Myint Thein and 60 years old Mya Thein from Kyon Par Village, Tin Myo Khaing, Win Zaw Htay and Hsan Shay from Hpoe Sa Bai Village; all of whom were killed during the interrogation. Of the 5 killed, only Kyaw Myint Thein's family was allowed to see his body at the hospital. His body was never returned to his family. The 4 remaining families were not allowed to see the bodies of their family members. Additionally, the families were not notified about deceased dates of the 4 people.

On June 20, at around 9:30 a.m., an artillery shell fired by the junta forces exploded inside Thar Si Village in Kale Township, Sagaing Region; killing a local man from artillery shrapnel while injuring a woman.

On June 9, around 100 junta personnel raided and stationed themselves in Nyaung Pin Gyi Village in Salingyi Township, Sagaing Region. From June 9 to 20, the junta personnel consistently conducted arson operations in the village. The body of mentally ill Kyaw Min Khaing was discovered with a gunshot wound and injuries consistent with torture.

On June 9, over 80 junta personnel raided Nyaung Pin Gyi Village, Salingyi Township, Sagaing Region. On June 19, the body of 70-year-old Tin Shwe was found in the village with gunshot wounds.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On the night of June 21, junta forces stationed at Technological University (Kalay) fired heavy artillery at San Thar (East) Village in Kale Township, Sagaing Region. As there were no recorded clashes in the region, the artillery attacks were indiscriminate in nature. An artillery shell struck a house in the village, killing a 5-year-old child due to shrapnel striking them on the head, while injuring three other family members.

On June 22, at approximately 8 a.m., around 70 junta personnel raided Ta Kaung Min Village in Wetlet Township, Sagaing Region. In addition to shooting and killing a local identified as Sein Myint, along with a goat herder identified as Naing Soe at the entrance to the village, the junta forces set 15 houses, a car and 9 motorbikes on fire.

On June 11, at around 1pm junta forces stationed themselves in Mhan Ban Village in Lashio Township, Shan State, and they got into direct clashes with Kokang Army (MNDAA) for over 3 hours. Afterwards, an artillery shell fired by the junta exploded on top of a house in the village, killing Mar Yoon, the mother of an 8-month-old child. The 8-month-old child was being treated at Lashio People's Hospital at the time of writing. 2 houses were destroyed by the artillery shell.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On the evening of June 24, No.264 Light Infantry Battalion of the junta forces in Peinzaloke Town and junta forces in Kyauktaga Town fired artillery shells at Ngar Pel Inn and Tha Min Inn Kone Villages in Kyauktaga Township, Bago Region. Artillery shells exploded at a football field inside Ngar Pel Inn Village, killing Saw Thar Ka Doe and Saw Mu Dee who were playing football, while injuring at least five people.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On June 25, around 30 personnel from the Artillery Unit of the junta forces fired artillery shells at Nit Ka Yin Village in Ye Township, Mon State. An artillery shell exploded on a house in the village, killing a local named Khin Hla Pyae Tut from artillery shrapnel, while 4 other people were injured.

On June 23, a clash broke out between junta personnel on a hidden watch and the People's Defence Force in Maung Ma Kan Village, Launglon Township, Tanintharyi Region. About an hour later, the junta forces shot and killed a local named Zaw Lat near a monastery in the village.

On June 16, while gardener Thar Chaung from Tanintharyi Town in Tanintharyi Region, was returning home from work, junta forces shot and killed him at a checkpoint at the entrance of Tanintharyi Town, for allegedly being part of the People's Defence Force (PDF). They also apprehended a man who was with him.

On June 25, at around 8 am, an estimated 200 junta personnel raided Kan Tharyar Village in Khin-U Township, Sagaing Region, after firing various weapons into the village. As a result, a local named Phoe Ko was killed by artillery shrapnel, while 2 other locals were seriously injured.

On the morning of June 24, over 100 junta personnel attacked Tae Su Village in Khin-U Township, Sagaing Region, and fired artillery shells into the village. As a result, a local named Moe Swe was killed immediately by artillery shrapnel while 9 other locals were injured.

On June 23, at around 4 a.m., junta forces dropped bombs from the aircraft on Lu Hku Pa Ra and Do Raw Villages in the western Hpruso Township, Kayah State, without any clash taking place. As a result, a local named Lwee Zi from Do Raw Village was killed and two others were injured.

On June 23 at around 10 pm, Regional Operations Command of the junta forces fired 120mm artillery shells at Hto Mar Village in Kale Township, Sagaing Region. As a result, a local named Win Bo was killed by exploding artillery shrapnel, while 4 other locals, including his wife, were seriously injured.

On June 24, at around 10 pm, 2 soldiers guarding the gates of a ward administration office of Ye Mun Taung Ward, near 35th and 59th Streets in Mahaaungmyay Township, Mandalay Region, shot at 18-year-old Sai Khant Kyaw. He was shot in the stomach and forearm and brought to the hospital, where he died from his injuries.

The junta then proceeded to raid Kin Taw Village. As a result, locals named Myint Kyaw Thu and Maung Sann were shot and killed. Moreover, the military reinforced themselves with an additional 50 personnel and raided Myin Sel Village in Sagaing Township. As a result, 69-year-old Pauk Sa was shot and killed, while 2 other men were injured.

As a result, 9 locals and a monk were killed. Additionally, two of the locals injured in the attack later died, bringing the total number of fatalities to 11. Due to the bombing, a monastery and 13 houses were also destroyed.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On July 1, at around 2 pm, junta forces fired 6 artillery shells at Pauk U Village in Yesagyo Township, Magway Region. An artillery shell exploded on a house, and the shrapnel killed a child named Hnin Shwe Yii Linn, who was 2 years and 5 months old.

On July 7, 2021, junta forces arrested Sein Win from Ma Kyee Su Village in Myingyan Township, Mandalay Region. He was sentenced to serve 3 years in prison under Section 505 a of the Penal Code. On the afternoon of July 2, 2023, the police station informed his family that he died from Gastrointestinal Bleeding while being detained in Myingyan Prison. They told the family that the body would be returned to them. However, when the family members went to retrieve his body from the mortuary, they were denied. On July 3, the junta forces cremated his body.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: Deputy Township Administrator Htay Linn Aung (aka Ba Maung) of Nawnghkio Town, Shan State joined CDM and on March 8, 2022, he was arrested by the junta forces at a checkpoint at the entrance of Kyaukme Town. Following his arrest, his family lost contact with him. In July 2023, his family learned that he died 6 days after his arrest during the interrogation.

On July 2, at around 11 am, the junta’s security police outpost at a bridge in Chaung Nit Kwa Village in Kyaikmaraw Township, Mon State, was attacked. Then the junta force opened fire indiscriminately. As a result, Nyein Chan Aung was shot and killed while returning to the village after accompanying his father to a rubber plantation.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldHfL2UA8oU0Imne: Khant Linn Naing (aka) Ko Khant (aka) Let Wae
cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ခန့်လင်းနိုင်(ခ) ကိုခန့် (ခ) လက်ဝဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On June 27, 2023, a number of prisoners, including Khant Linn Naing, Aung Myo Thu, Pyae Phyo Hein and Min Bhone Ma Har were removed from Daik-U Prison. Since their removal, their whereabouts have remained unknown, with no information regarding their current location.In the first week of July 2023, officials from Daik-U Prison dispatched signed letters to the families of Khant Linn Naing (aka Ko Khant, aka Let Wel), the son of Than Soe Naing, Pyae Phyo Hein (aka Ko Pyae), the son of Kyaw Oo and Aung Myo Thu, the son of Maung Sein. The letters were sent to inform the families of the prisoners' deaths. In the second week of July, Daik-U Prison dispatched five additional signed letters to the families of Zin Myint Htun (aka Yar Lay), the son of Myint Than, Nay Aye (aka Arkar Htet Paing Myo), the son of Myo Linn (aka Nay Myo), Jar Gyi (aka Wai Yan Lwin), the son of Aye Lwin, Zin Win Htut (aka Ba La Gyi, aka Ta Yote Gyi), the son of Pyant Maw and Bo Bo Win (aka Htan Taw Gyi). The letters were delivered to inform the families of the prisoners' deaths. According to the letters' contents, a transport vehicle used for transfers from Daik-U Prison to Insein Prison, was involved in an accident. Seizing the opportunity, the prisoners allegedly attempted to escape. They were killed by security forces who claimed to have fired warning shots at the prisoners in an attempt to recapture them.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On May 25, junta personnel dragged out around 20 political prisoners in Daik-U Prison, Daik-U Township, Bago Region, and interrogated them. Thant Zin Win, who was sentenced to serve over 80 years in prison under Section 505, 51, 52, 54 and so on, disappeared since then. According to reports, it is known that Ko Thant Zin Win was killed by junta troops. It is known that the military informed his family that he had died of heatstroke. As a result, they were shot dead while the junta forces tried to re-apprehend them.

In October 2021, junta forces arrested Maung Than Soe from Nar Din Village in Minbya Township, Rakhine State for alleged connection with Arakan Army (AA). He was facing trial at Ann Township Court under the charge of Section 17(1) of the Unlawful Associations Act. While being detained at Ann Myoma Police Station, he began suffering from a fever and had difficulty breathing. Because of this, his family asked for him to receive medical treatment but the junta refused. On July 1, 2023, he had difficulty breathing again and despite the junta sending him to hospital, he died because he was treated in time.

On June 27, 2023, some prisoners including Khant Linn Naing, Aung Myo Thu, Pyae Phyo Hein and Min Bhone Ma Har, were removed from Daik-U Prison. Since then, their whereabouts were unknown, without any trace of information on their location. On the first week of  July 2023, Daik-U Prison sent signed letters to the family of Khant Linn Naing (aka Ko Khant, aka Let Wel), the son of Than Soe Naing, the family of Pyae Phyo Hein (aka Aung Pyae), the son of Kyaw Oo, and the family of Aung Myo Thu, the son of Maung Sein, respectively to inform them of their deaths. On the second week of July, the prison sent another two signed letters to the family of Zin Myint Tun (aka Yar Lay), the son of Myint Thein, respectively to inform them of their deaths. According to the letters, while transferring prisoners from Daik-U Prison to another prison, a transport vehicle was involved in an accident. Seizing the opportunity, the prisoners allegedly attempted to escape. As a result, they were killed by the security forces who fired “warning shots” at them in an attempt to recapture.

On the morning of July 11, junta forces, stationed in Tar Han Ward in Kale Town, Sagaing Region, fired artillery shells indiscriminately. The shells exploded in Taung Pee Lar Ward in the same town, killing a woman immediately, while a student was also injured from artillery shrapnel.

The four of them were sent to Kutkai Public Hospital for treatment, where the 16-year-old boy later died from his injuries.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On the morning of August 10, junta forces were inspecting passing vehicles in Taung Pee Lar Ward, Kale Town, Sagaing Region. Two men who were driving on a motorbike saw the soldiers and tried to turn around, causing the soldiers to shoot at them. As a result, Salai Cung Lian Bik from Mon Htar Ywar Thit Village was killed immediately, while another man was shot in the arm

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ရီအောင်ဝင်း
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On August 4, Nam Hkam Myoma militiamen, subservient to the junta arrested a Hseng Hsat Villager and 3 locals from Man Kan Villages for allegedly being affiliated with the TNLA. They were arrested while returning from Pan Hkam Village, Se Lant Village Tract, Muse Township in Shan State. The man from Man Kan Village died due to torture during interrogation, which involved denial of food. The other three were tortured as well, and on the evening of August 10, they were discarded at a garbage pile near Man Mai Village.

On August 11, junta forces and Pyu Saw Htee members fired 120mm artillery shells from Myauk Khin Yan Village and targeted Myin Thar Village in Gangaw Township, Magway Region. An artillery shell exploded in the village, killing a woman immediately from shrapnel strikes to the head.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: အမည်စုံစမ်းဆဲ
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On August 5, at 6:15 a.m., the junta's Mar Lar Oo checkpoint in Kyaukkyi Township, Bago Region was attacked. In retaliation, the junta forces fired artillery shells and gunfire into Baw Di Kone Village in Thay Waw Dae Village Tract, Kyaukkyi Township. An 8-year-old child from Pay Tue Village, who had been seeking refuge in Baw Di Kone Village, was killed from artillery shrapnel.

On August 13, at around 6 p.m., around 30 junta personnel raided and opened fire at U Yin Su Village, No.7 Ward, Yesagyo Township, Magway Region. As a result, a person from Htan Chaung Village, who was living in U Yin Su Village was killed by getring shot in the head and stomach.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldtemYeWjXl02LvL: ဇော်ကိုလတ်
cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On August 11, around 100 junta personnel raided Wetlet Township in Sagaing Region. They arrested and killed an individual with mental health problems, a disabled individual, and two members of People’s Defence Team (PDT). The individual with mental health problems was unable to escape, and was handcuffed behind his back. His throat was slit by the junta, and the disabled individual was shot in the head. The deceased were from Peitthugyi Village in Wetlet Township. On August 13, their dead bodies were found in the village. The bodies of the two PDT members were found on the same day in the lake near Htan Gyi Village. Their hands were handcuffed behind their backs, their faces were bruised and they had gunshot wounds to the chest.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On August 17, at around 11 p.m, junta forces raided a house in Mya Kan Thar Ward, Khin-U Town, Sagaing Region, killing a 3-year-old twin child and a man from gunfire. The twin was shot in the head. The junta forces took away their bodies. Additionally, the junta forces arrested the other twin, their mother and a member of an urban guerrillas. On the afternoon of August 19, the body of the captive male was discovered inside Maha Nandar Kan Daw Canal in Shwebo Township. The other twin was released on the evening of August 18, while his mother was still detained at Myoma Police Station.

cellValuesByColumnId.fldjrwtsuYe3r5QOW: On the morning of August 17, a military column of around 80 junta personnel attacked Ta Moke Chone Village in Tanintharyi Township, Tanintharyi Region. At around 8 pm that day, a local named Tun Naing Win was shot dead after encountering the junta forces. The junta took away his body.

On August 19, at 3:40 pm, junta forces, stationed in Palaw Township, Taninthary Region, fired 120mm artillery shells indiscriminately. An artillery shell exploded in Let Ku Village, and  75-year-old Than Kyi was killed instantly when artillery shrapnel struck her neck. Three other locals were also injured.
